title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 8 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Into mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Add raisins and caraway seed, mixing well to coat the raisins with flour.
Combine the eggs, buttermilk and butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix lightly only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake in preheated oven for about 1 hour.
Makes one loaf.
(Test with toothpick.)

title: chili (without beans)
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onions; cook until tender, not brown.
Add beef; cook until browned (drain if necessary). Add tomatoes, ketchup, beer, salt, Tabasco and chili powder. Crush garlic and add.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: For sauce, in a small saucepan, stir together milk, flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder, if desired.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in onion.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick spray coating.
Place half of the potatoes in the casserole.
Top with half of the sauce. Repeat layers with remaining potatoes and sauce.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven about 65 minutes, or until potatoes are tender, stirring once.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
If desired, garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and almonds.
Combine butter, soup, liquid and cheese in saucepan.
Heat until blended.
Alternate asparagus, sauce and cracker crumbs, making 2 layers of each.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: mock country fried steak
directions: Mix flour, milk, salt, pepper and Accent together.
Knead into meat thoroughly.
Sprinkle excess flour on dough board.
Knead. Roll out 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick.
Cut into various size pieces. Brown in hot grease.
Remove and make gravy.
Drop meat back into gravy.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture will form a ball (3 to 4 minutes).
Drop on waxed paper.
Knead in food color.
This will keep several months, if stored in an airtight container.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Fry okra in 2 tablespoons shortening.
In a
large pot, make roux by cooking 2 tablespoons shortening and 2 tablespoons flour until dark brown. Add onions and celery to roux.
Cook until soft, about 5 minutes. Add okra.
Stir in tomatoes, parsley, bay leaf, thyme and water. Simmer 30 minutes. Add peeled, deveined shrimp and crabs.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: pork chop casserole a la sibyl
directions: Place rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour margarine over rice. Combine soup mix and water and cook until hot.
Pour over rice. Season pork chops.
Lay on top of rice.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour at 400°.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, oil and water. In large bowl mix dry ingredients together. Add creamed mixture. Mix well. Makes 3 bread pan loafs. Bake at 350° for 1 - 1 1\2 hours.

title: bean gravy
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until nearly done.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: crab pastries
directions: Mix all filling ingredients in medium bowl.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into rectangles, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Spread the filling to within 1/4-inch of dough edge.
Fold dough over, covering completely, seal well. Brush with melted butter and roll in potato chips.
Place on ungreased baking sheet, bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown, slice while warm.

title: jeanette's potato salad
directions: Use small California (size B) potatoes.
Cook with skin on. Boil for approximately 30 minutes, until fork-tender (not soft). Peel and cut when cool (next day).
Mix lightly potatoes, celery and onion.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add salt, baking powder and soda.
Add flour, buttermilk and mashed bananas. Add vanilla.
Pour into three greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice with caramel icing.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream in mixing bowl the sugar, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add applesauce.
In another bowl, sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Combine flour mixture with creamed mixture and beat.
Add raisins.
Put in floured and greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Cool in pan on wire rack. Wrap in aluminum foil.
Better a day or two after baked.

title: punch for 100
directions: Combine sugar, Kool-Aid and just enough warm water to mix.
Add the rest of the water and pineapple juice.
Chill overnight.
Add one ginger ale to 3 quarts of punch at serving time.

title: poor man's cake(depression cake)
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together. Add rest of the ingredients. Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch ungreased pan. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: special k patties(good)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a medium bowl and shape with hands into small patties.
Fry in a little oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Place in a casserole dish with sauce.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: glorified rice
directions: Drain pineapple, measuring syrup.
Add water to pineapple syrup to make 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil; stir in Minute rice.
Cover.
Turn off heat.
Let set 7 minutes, all the time necessary for the rice to absorb the tart sweet fruit flavor. Drain cherries and dice; add to your pineapple.
Stir in rice. Fold in Cool Whip.
Let cool.
Keep in fridge and have a tasty dish whenever you please.

title: cold vegetable salad
directions: Make 2 or more layers.
Prepare at least 8 hours before serving (covered tight).

title: kiss'n cuz'n sourdough bread
directions: Stir ingredients with plastic or wood utensil.
(Metal kills the fermenting process.)
Let set unrefrigerated for 18 to 24 hours to ferment.
Must be fed every 3 to 5 days, adding the above mentioned ingredients over again.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package. Cool cake slightly. Poke holes in cake with wooden spoon.

Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut together and pour over cake so that it fills all holes. Refrigerate before serving. Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut or mix these two together and frost.

title: perfect scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters; reserve 1/4 cup liquid. Combine crumbs and butter. Spread 1/3 crumbs in greased 8x1 1/4 inch baking dish. Cover with 1/2 the oysters. Sprinkle with pepper. Spread another 1/3 crumbs; cover with remaining oysters. Sprinkle with pepper.

title: parmesan fish
directions: Score
fillets.
Put
in buttered baking dish. Salt and pepper.
Mix
mayonnaise,
cheese,	onion,	basil and parsley. Spread
on fish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: fresh apple cake 2
directions: Combine the sugar, oil and eggs in a bowl and mix well.
Sift flour with soda and salt; stir into the sugar mixture.
Add apples and 1 cup nuts; beat well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; cool.
Soften the cream cheese into a bowl.
Add margarine and cream well.
Add vanilla.
Add powdered sugar alternately with milk and stir in remaining nuts.
Spread between layers and over top and sides of cake.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, salt, pepper, onion and corn flakes.
Mix well and form into balls.
Place in baking dish.
Combine soups and water; pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: carrots and sugar snap peas
directions: Combine carrots and water in a 2 1/2-quart glass baking dish. Cover with plastic wrap, leaving one corner loose for steam to escape, or cover with glass cover.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring after three minutes.
Stir in peas and seasonings.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute, covered.
Stir and serve.
Toss with fresh mint, if desired.

title: tomato pickles
directions: Mix water and lime well.
Then add tomatoes and soak 24 hours. Drain and change in fresh cold water 3 times, leaving one hour between changes.
Drain the last time real good.
Mix white vinegar and sugar.
Add tomatoes and let soak overnight.
Simmer about 1 hour or until color has changed.
Then seal in hot jars.

title: garlic parmesan rolls
directions: Cut dough into 16 pieces.
Shape into balls.
Place on a floured surface.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 10 minutes.
In a bowl, stir Parmesan cheese and garlic powder into butter using a spoon.
Roll balls in butter mixture; arrange loosely in a 9-inch round baking pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Warm leftover butter mixture.
When rolls are baked, pull them apart and dip them again.
Serve warm.
Yield: 16 rolls.

title: russian tea (non-alcoholic drink)
directions: Mix thoroughly and store in airtight container.
(Will keep indefinitely.)
Use 2 teaspoons Russian tea to 1 cup boiling water.
May be served hot or chilled.

title: fresh orange bavarian
directions: Pour boiling water over jello in bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in sugar, orange peel and juice.
Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
In chilled bowl, beat whipping cream until stiff. (If using dessert topping mix, prepare as directed on package.) Beat gelatin mixture until foamy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 4 cup mold or 6 to 8 dessert dishes or molds.
Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Unmold on serving plate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate-peanut balls
directions: Partially melt chocolate pieces in the top of a double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Remove from hot water and stir rapidly until chocolate is entirely melted.
Stir in milk, peanuts and vanilla.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape each into a ball.
If desired, decorate with colored sugar or candied cherries.
Chill again until firm.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: famous southwestern salad
directions: Mix lime juice, olive oil and garlic cloves to make dressing. Toss last 5 ingredients. Add dressing to tossed ingredients just before serving.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Pour Jell-O in large bowl.
Add 2 cups hot water.
Mix until Jell-O dissolves.
Add cranberry sauce, small amount at a time. Mix until dissolved.
Add sour cream, small amounts at a time. Pour into Jell-O mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: romaine and strawberry salad
directions: Mix romaine, lettuce, strawberries, and onion.
Set aside. For dressing, mix olive oil, vinegar, sugar, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
This makes double the amount of dressing that you need. Pour dressing over greens before serving.
Toss to coat.

title: stuffed pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Brown sausage and ground beef in skillet until crumbly; drain and set aside.
Mix Bisquick and water until dough forms.
Divide into 2 parts with 1 slightly larger than the other.
Press larger piece of dough in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish and press the dough up the sides of the dish.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes.
Start timing after mixture reaches a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Stir until blended, then drop on waxed paper by teaspoonfuls.
Coconut or chopped dates may be added if desired.
May be placed in fridge to hasten.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Beat in sugar until thick and sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla and cream.
Mix well and add pudding.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add cookies.
Add milk to fill the container.
Freeze.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, 1/3 cup butter and egg.
Add buttermilk, flour, baking powder and baking soda and salt.
Pour half of batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons soft butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle half of topping over batter.
Add rest of batter and sprinkle with remaining topping.
Sprinkle additional cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325° for glass pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and bone it.
Take the chicken broth and cook spaghetti in it.
In a large baking dish combine cream of mushroom and chicken soups, onions, butter, spaghetti and chicken; mix well.
On top of mixture sprinkle grated cheese and crumbled chips or corn flakes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat banana nut bread(yields 1 loaf)
directions: Cream applesauce and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add flour alternately with bananas, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour in loaf pan and bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except spinach.
Mix well.
Fold in spinach.
Chill for 2 hours.
Take 1 loaf round sourdough bread and hollow out center.
Cut center into cubes.
Put dip into center of bread.
Arrange bread pieces around outside.
Dip into loaf with bread pieces.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients except coconut.
Make balls and roll in coconut.

title: make-ahead potatoes
directions: Mash all ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes.
You might wish to sprinkle finely chopped green onions on top of casserole.
This dish can be made a day ahead and refrigerated.
Bring back to room temperature before baking.
It can be frozen, thawed and baked and will taste fresh made.
Bake at 350° until hot and slightly brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding and milk. Beat until thick, then fold in Cool Whip. In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer bottom with graham crackers. Pour pudding mixture over crackers. Then add another layer of graham crackers, a layer of pudding and end with crackers. Top with the can of icing.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper into a 1-quart pan. Stir the beet liquid, vinegar and orange concentrate into sugar mixture.
Cover.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until mixture is glossy and slightly thickened, stirring twice.
Add sliced beets and heat until beets are hot.
Sprinkle orange rind over top before serving.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and whipped cream.
Mix the peanut butter, powdered sugar, cream cheese and whipped cream in large bowl.
Add as much milk as is needed to make the mixture soft and creamy. Dump into pie crust.
Freeze 6 to 8 hours.
Remove from freezer; let stand for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil;
Sift together, flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually add to sugar mixture, while mixing,
then add carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Grease and flour 3 cake pans.
Divide batter into pans,
bake at 350 degrees for 30 min.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: garden fresh ham and rice salad
directions: In large bowl, combine celery, onion, mayonnaise and dill. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates. Serves 4 to 6.

title: christmas coffee cake
directions: Beat margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Add sour cream.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Spoon half of batter into angel cake pan, greased and floured.
In small dish, mix cinnamon and 4 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle half of this over batter and a handful of raisins and walnuts.
Add rest of batter, rest of cinnamon-sugar mixture and another 1/2 cup chopped nuts (raisins optional).
Place in cold oven; set oven for 350° and bake about 1 hour.

title: moussaka stir-fry
directions: In a large bowl, mix beef, garlic powder, oregano and pepper. In a medium size bowl mix broth, tomato paste and sour cream. Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large deep skillet over high heat until hot but not smoking.
Add meat mixture and stir-fry, breaking up with a large spoon until no longer pink.
Spoon into a large bowl.
Heat remaining oil in the skillet.
Add eggplant and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes until slightly softened.
Add bell peppers and stir-fry about 1 minute, until crisp-tender and eggplant is tender.
Add to beef mixture.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix as given.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: baked sauerkraut wirth
directions: Spread the sauerkraut in a buttered ovenproof serving dish 12 x 9 x 2-inch.
Cover it with tomatoes, including the reserved juice.
Sprinkle the mixture with brown sugar.
Arrange the bacon on top and bake in a preheated oven at 300° for 2 hours.
Remove from oven, cut the bacon into pieces and stir it gently into the sauerkraut mixture.
Bake the dish, adding water as necessary to prevent it from drying out for 1 more hour.
Serves 8.
Always a hit at covered dish suppers and cookouts!
Nice vegetable with pork or beef.

title: french onion soup(microwave)
directions: Chop onions. Add 1 cup water and microwave in a covered dish for 25 minutes (High power). Add beef consomme, 2 cans of water, basil, thyme, bay leaves and salt and pepper to taste.
Microwave for 30 minutes (High power).

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix butter and cracker crumbs together.
Press in bottom of pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Spread over crumb crust.
Then slice bananas over sugar mixture, then spread pineapple over bananas.
Now put Cool Whip over top and chill for 4 hours before serving.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries, if desired.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions. Punch holes in cake, then let cool. In a separate bowl, combine 1 pkg. orange jello with hot water until dissolved. Add 1 cup cold milk. Pour over cake and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours. Combine 1 pkg. orange jello, vanilla, pudding, and milk. Mix until creamy, fold in cool whip and ice the cake. Keep refrigerated.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients. Refrigerate. Makes 8 servings.

title: so-o-o-o good pork chops
directions: Whip eggs with water to make egg wash.
Mix remaining ingredients together, except for oil, and place on plate.
Dip chops into egg wash, then into coating mix.
Pan-fry in oil until golden brown.

title: coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 3 (9 inch) cake pans. Using an electric mixer, cream butter until fluffy. Add sugar and continue to cream well for 6 to 8 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour and milk alternately to creamed mixture, beginning with flour. Add vanilla and continue to beat until just mixed. Divide batter equally among prepared pans. Level batter in each pan by holding pan 3 or 4 inches above counter, then dropping it flat onto counter. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough; do not let rise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut one loaf into small pieces.
Place here and there in pan. Melt butter; add brown sugar, pudding mix, milk and cinnamon. Beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour over the pieces of one loaf. Then cut up second loaf and place on top in empty spaces.
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes. Cool for 10 to 15 minutes and turn out of pan.

title: chicken primavera
directions: In skillet, blend first 3 ingredients; stir in chicken and vegetables.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Pray.
Grease 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
Line bottom with waxed paper and grease again.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using oil, eggs and juice drained from mandarin oranges.
Stir in oranges and nuts.
Bake n a 325° preheated oven for 25 minutes or until a pick comes out clean. Cool on racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and peel off paper.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients except the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Five minutes before done, sprinkle the Mozzarella cheese on and continue baking the alloted time.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Mix jello, sugar and boiling water.
After it is mixed well, cream in the cream cheese.
Have Pet milk very cold and beat until stiff.
Mix in jello mixture.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat undiluted soup and green chilies in saucepan.
Place cheese, chicken, onion and a spoonful of sauce in a tortilla. Roll up and place in a baking dish.
Repeat with the 9 remaining tortillas.
Pour the remaining sauce over the top.
Sprinkle leftovers on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Saute beef, bacon and onion together.
Drain all beans, except pork and beans.
Mix ingredients together.
Bake in crock-pot for 6 hours or in oven for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna pate
directions: Beat together with electric beater cream cheese, chili sauce, finely chopped parsley, minced onion, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Drain tuna and gradually add to the cream cheese mixture, beating until thoroughly blended.
Chill well before serving. Serve with crisp crackers.

title: pilaf
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart size pot.
Add vermicelli (crushed into 3/4-inch size) and brown, stirring constantly, until near burning point.
Add rice; stir.
Add chicken broth, chicken bouillon, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Cover and cook until all broth has been absorbed.
Stir occasionally.
Cook over low heat, about 20 minutes.
Turn heat off and let sit about 10 minutes.
Serves 6. Good with chicken or fish.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with shortening or vegetable spray/oil.

title: marshmallow fluff
directions: Mix well in bowl; cover and set in refrigerator overnight.

title: beef stew
directions: Flour meat and brown. Add to rest of ingredients.
Put in a 2-quart deep oven baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: death-by-chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare batter as directed on package and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chocolate chips over batter.
Bake 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon.
Pour warmed hot fudge sauce over cake and spread evenly.
Cool; frost with whipped topping and garnish with chocolate sprinkles.
Refrigerate.

title: laplands
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon-colored, 4 to 5 minutes. Blend in flour, milk, sugar, butter and salt.
Beat 2 to 3 minutes.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Fill 2 well-greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with butter or jam.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Combine sugar and flour, crushed pineapple and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into large casserole dish and top with crackers. Drizzle butter over top.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: pinto bean soup
directions: If you're cooking a big pot of beans, use 2 pounds hamburger meat.
Add tomato sauce to beans.

title: goober cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and sour cream.
Add instant pudding and next the chocolate chips.
Blend mixture until thoroughly melted.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a greased Bundt pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Spread in 9 x 13 inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top if desired. Bake at 350° 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 X 13 pan, dump in (do not mix) pineapple, cherry filling, white cake mix, evenly to make one layer of each. Drizzle margarine over top, then add nuts.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350 degrees.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Beat eggs, sugar and oleo.
Add apples, flour, salt, soda and spices.
Bake 1 hour.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts to a pulp.
Add other ingredients, except bacon.
Add bacon last, crumbling on top.
Chill well. Serve with Melba rounds.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well and marinate for at least 1 hour, before serving.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in saucepan; blend in milk and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils; boil for 1 minute (stirring).
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream, cake and ice cream or cake and Cool Whip.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Using palm of hand, flatten chicken to even thickness.
Dip chicken into egg, then into crumbs to coat.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Put in blender and mix thoroughly.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook the onion in butter until tender. Add all remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings (2 quarts).

title: no frost oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and let stand 10 minutes.
Add sugars, shortening and eggs.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to oatmeal mixture.
Pour into baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease baking pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Melt chocolate and shortening in large saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top of batter.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: hot! hot! wings
directions: You will need a deep fryer, oven or barbecue grill.

title: oma's chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine and stir by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate-butterscotch pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Butter an 8-inch round cake pan. In a medium bowl, thoroughly blend the flour, 1/2 cup of the brown sugar, 1/4 cup of the cocoa, the coffee, baking powder and salt. Stir in the butterscotch chips. In a small bowl, blend the milk, oil and vanilla. Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients and stir until blended. Pour the batter into the prepared cake pan and spread it evenly. Blend together the remaining 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Sprinkle this mixture on top of the cake batter. Pour the hot water evenly over the surface of the batter. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until the top looks cake like and dry. Serve the pudding cake with whipped cream if desired.

title: corn pudding
directions: Spray a dish with Pam.
Mix corns in a bowl with crackers crumbled up, then pour into dish for the oven.
Top corns with stick of butter in pats over the top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice thinly.
Dissolve sugar in vinegar and toss slices in marinade.
Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: siapo dough
directions: Mix yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Combine flour, sugar, warm milk and oil.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture.
Knead dough just as for bread.
Let dough rise in bowl, covered with a cloth for 1 hour.
Dough should double in size.
Knead dough again to get rid of air bubbles.
Shape into long rolls, resembling a sausage.
Cut into slices; roll them flat.
Put a spoonful of filling on dough and fold up edges to enclose filling.
Pinch dough together.
Form a ball.
Cut small circles from waxed paper, approximately 2-inches round, just large enough for rolls to sit on.
Place waxed paper and rolls on a rack inside a steamer. Steam for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 20 Siapo.

title: five cheese spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix cheeses together in bowl. Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle garlic, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce on bottom of dish.
Make 3 layers of spaghetti, salt and pepper, paprika, cheese and dot with butter. Pour milk over all.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stir from bottom, recover with foil, return to oven for 20 minutes.
Stir and bake 15 minutes.

title: date loaf
directions: In a skillet, combine sugar, syrup and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add dates and mash until well mixed.
Add nuts and vanilla. Beat until carameled.
Roll onto wet cheesecloth.
Let chill until cool.
Unwrap and slice.

title: crackers
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until the pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over flour mixture.
Toss lightly with a fork. Continue adding water gradually and tossing quickly until dough holds together.
Chill dough 5 minutes.
Roll on floured board until very thin.
Cut into 1-inch wide strips and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until tips of crackers are golden brown.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic over medium heat.
Add next 7 ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with torn tortillas.
Top with meat mixture and more tortillas. (Layer meat and tortillas.)
Pour soup and milk mixed over and top with layer of cheese sprinkled evenly over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage balls
directions: Set sausage and cheese out to get at room temperature. Mix all together. Roll into balls about the size of a walnut. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit cheesecake
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 15-inch baking pan.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to 16 to 20 graham crackers rolled fine.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 15-inch pan.

title: standard biscuits
directions: Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk all at once and mix just until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out on floured surface; knead gently 1/2 minute.
Roll or pat 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in hot oven (450°) 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16 medium sized biscuits.

title: fried wonton
directions: Brown meat in oil until brown and crumbly.
Add diced water chestnuts and 1 onion.
Season with soy sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch dissolved in sake.
Add green onions and cook for 1 minute.
Let it cool.

title: sharon rainey's strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and mix well.
Put into 2 small greased and floured pans.
Fill about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Serve plain or with confectioners icing.

title: pretzel salad surprise
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups hot water. Stir in strawberries until almost set.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzels, sugar and butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 8 minutes. Remove and cool. Beat cream cheese and sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread on top of Jell-O mixture.

title: au gratin of cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; add garlic, saute.
Stir in ham; saute.
Add cauliflower; saute.
Stir in flour and cream. Blend in seasonings.
Heat to boil, then remove immediately.
Pour into au gratin dish.
Mix in cheese and top with parsley.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients to oats.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Place chicken in 9 x 12-inch pan. Combine soup and sour cream.
Mix well and stir in poppy seed. Spread evenly over chicken.
Crumble crackers and spread over chicken.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: easy cowboy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine butter, milk, and muffin mix.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet by heaping tablespoons.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10-12 minutes, or until edges are golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes, remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 9 cookies, but they can be made smaller.

title: lamb curry
directions: Brown lamb lightly in butter.
Add onions.
Add curry, garlic, salt and apple.
Simmer with lid on until apple and onion are tender.
Add tomatoes.
Cover; cook until lamb is tender, about 1 hour.
If not thick enough, cook a few minutes at higher heat to reduce.
Add grapes just before serving.
When they are completely heated through, serve with rice and accompany with a good chutney.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; let cool, then peel and coarsely shred.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish greased with the 1/4 teaspoon butter.

In a saucepan over low heat, combine the cheese, butter, soup and milk, stirring until cheese is melted. Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper; pour over top of potatoes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to cook, sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir, just enough to mix spices.
Cover, set on low setting and cook for 10 to 12 hours, then on high setting for 5 to 6 hours.

title: easy cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in water until tender; drain and place cabbage in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in a saucepan; add soup, cheese, sugar and salt.
Heat gently until cheese is melted.
Pour over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 2 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, cola, water and syrup.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and food coloring as desired.
Let cool.
Place berries in crusts and pour cooled sauce over top.
Refrigerate until completely cooled. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: b & b's cajun fish
directions: Mix 1/2 part mustard and 1/2 part Louisiana hot sauce together in a large bowl.
Mix 1/2 part corn meal and 1/2 part cracker meal together in large cake pan.
Add Tony Chachere Creole seasoning and black pepper to the meal mix per your taste preference and mix together.
Roll fish into meal until they are completely covered by the meal.
Remember to sift meal frequently to remove lumps.
Fry fish in hot peanut oil.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan.
Add Texas Pete and mix well.
Keep warm on low heat, stirring occasionally to keep mixed well.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Cream potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream and butter.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Put in baking dish; top with butter and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut salad
directions: Soak marshmallows in cream or milk for 5 minutes.
Pour all ingredients together, except milk from marshmallows, and mix.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch prepared pan, greased and floured.

title: peach bundt cake
directions: Combine
all of the ingredients in a bowl and beat with an electric
mixer.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake approximately 60 minutes at 350°.
Cool in the pan.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Combine the cranberries, 1/3 cup sugar, margarine and pecans and put into bottom of pan.
Combine all the rest of the ingredients together and pour on top of other.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until brown.

title: reese's cup cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cracker crumbs, peanuts, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar in small bowl.
Press into 9-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and vanilla into large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well.
Toss peanut butter cups and 1 tablespoon flour in small bowl.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake 1 hour.
Chill. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef until done.
Place remaining ingredients in kettle or large pot.
Add ground beef.
Heat.
Season to taste. Serve with oyster crackers.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well in small bowl.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs and banana well; add to flour and mix well again.
Add vanilla.
Spray pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Check with toothpick to see if done.
Contains 120 calories per serving, 4 grams fat and 19.4 grams carbohydrates.

title: melt-in-your-mouth cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light. Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop by scant teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake in 400° oven about 5 minutes.
Cool slightly (1/2 minute).
Remove to wire rack.

title: chicken n' dressing
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except the chicken.
Pour 5 to 6 cups chicken broth over and mix well with potato masher to a thick batter consistency.
Mix the ingredients right into the baking pan.
After mixing, press the chicken pieces into the mixture, almost covering the chicken.
Add a little more broth to the top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown or set.
Serve with giblet gravy.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits, roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Place in greased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine and brown sugar luster.
Boil for 2 minutes then pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool before turning out on plate.

title: dark zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and brown sugar.
Add vanilla, zucchini and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into batter. Add nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured cake pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili
directions: In nonstick skillet over medium high heat, brown beef until almost done (no pink) and drain.
Add onions and cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Add garlic, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 20 minutes. Stir in chili powder, cayenne pepper, oregano, salt and pinto beans.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Combine cornstarch with cold water.
Stir into chili to thicken, cook additional 3 to 4 minutes.

title: "best ever" pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add butter, salt-flour mixture, syrup and nuts.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Add 1/2 cup pecan halves to top.
Bake pie at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 50 minutes.
Good alone or with a big scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: easy cheesy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except cheese and mix well.
In shallow baking dish, shape half the mixture into loaf.
Cut 4 slices of cheese into strips and arrange on meat.
Top with remaining meat and press edges together to seal.
Bake 1 hour; pour off fat.
Top with remaining cheese slices.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lynn's chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until done; skin and debone, reserving chicken broth.
Shred or cut into small strips.
Saute onion in the butter until soft and clear.
In a large casserole, layer some of the onion mixture, chicken and 1/2 of the package of stuffing.
Mix the can of celery soup and 1 can of broth.
Pour over the first layer of chicken casserole.
Layer another layer of onion, chicken and the rest of the stuffing.
Mix the remaining can of soup with 1 can of broth; pour over the casserole.
Bake, covered, for about 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover; top with grated cheese and bake an additional 15 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Cook for 10 minutes at 375°.
Reduce heat to 300 and cook 30 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat.
Cool.
Beat eggs until light at medium speed.
Add chocolate mixture, sugar, salt, vanilla and Karo.
Mix until blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour. Dissolve the soda in buttermilk. Combine water, oleo, cocoa and shortening; bring to
a boil.
Add flour-sugar mixture; blend well.
Add eggs, buttermilk and cinnamon.
Pour into a 12 x 6 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not remove from pan.

title: thumbprint cookies(these are a molded cookie)
directions: You will need an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl. Blend eggs with fork. Add oil and blend again. Add all to dry ingredients and mix with wire whip until smooth. Add and blend buttermilk. pour equally into three greased and floured 8" cake pans. Bake at 350 for 30 minutes. Cool ten minutes and remove from pans. Icing Mix together until light and fluffy:

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt butter. Add brown sugar and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and bring to boil again. Add vanilla and confectioners sugar. Beat until smooth.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast into warm water, then add flour, salt and sugar.
Take a piece and roll it into the shape you want.
Brush with beaten egg and then sprinkle on kosher salt.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 425° oven.
Serves 12.

title: turkey vegetable soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add onions; saute until translucent.
Stir in flour.
Add broth, potatoes, carrots, celery and poultry seasoning.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add turkey and half and half.
Add seasonings.
Cover and continue simmering until heated through. Serve hot.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine sugar with Italian dressing.
Add sweetened Italian dressing to drained spaghetti and mix thoroughly.
Next add the chopped vegetables and salad seasoning.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: In a separate bowl, combine hamburger, rice, eggs, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Mix well.

Separate leaves (using large leaves only) and parboil for about 5 minutes. Making individually, put about 2 tablespoons of hamburger mixture in the center of each leaf, roll up tightly, and secure with a toothpick.

title: fiesta ranch green chili dip
directions: Combine dip mix with sour cream.
Stir in chiles, olives and cheese. Serve with tortilla chips, vegetables or crackers.

title: venison sausage
directions: First Day:
Mix in large bowl; cover and refrigerate.

title: baked potato slices
directions: Place potato slices on well-buttered cookie sheet.
Butter top and sides generously.
Season to taste, sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until done and nicely browned.

title: perfect pecan pie
directions: Combine and heat first 5 items.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In large pan, cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Add undiluted cream of celery, mushroom and chicken.
Add remaining ingredients, except for dried onions.
Stir until mixed well. Pour noodles into casserole dish.
Top with dried onions.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: green chicken enchiladas
directions: In a large bowl, mix chicken, chiles, oregano and 2 cups of the cheese.
Season to taste with salt.
Pour oil to a depth of about 1/4 inch in an 8 to 10-inch skillet.
When oil is hot, cook each tortilla, turning once, just until limp (about 10 seconds per side).
Add more oil, as needed.
Drain on paper towels.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk to yeast mixture and set aside.

title: rhubarb raisin pie
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in egg, cracker crumbs, raisins and butter.
Pour into a pastry-lined 9 inch pie plate; cover with top crust.
Bake in hot (400°) oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Add salt to cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Then squeeze out and add carrot and green pepper.
While cabbage is standing, make syrup of water, vinegar, sugar, celery salt and mustard seed.
Mix and boil one minute.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Pour over cabbage mixture, put into containers and freeze.

title: baked bear chops
directions: Place the chops in a baking pan, salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle a teaspoon of brown sugar over each chop and top with slice of lemon.
Cover the chops with a mixture of equal parts ketchup and water.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours or until tender.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer for 6 hours.

title: cocktail tidbits
directions: Mix together.
Place in a shallow pan.
Bake at 200° for about 1 hour.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, margarine, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour filling into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: fiesta pie
directions: Mash avocados; combine with lemon juice.
Spread evenly in 9-inch pie plate.
Spread sour cream on top of avocados.
Sprinkle with onions.
Spoon taco sauce over onions; sprinkle with cheese, olives and tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time. Serve with chips for dipping.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat.
Add green pepper and onion; saute with meat.
Add soup or sauce and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles until done.
Drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place noodles in bottom. Pour meat sauce over top.
Sprinkle cheeses and mushrooms.
Cover and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add syrup, well beaten eggs and vanilla.
When well mixed, add coarsely chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in oven 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with liquid ingredients and stir until smooth.
Can top with chocolate chips for frosting.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 9-inch square pan.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large bowl stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk, and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Add to cabbage and carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss well and serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and peanut butter; add dry ingredients. Mix well.
Add vanilla and bake.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Place warm water in bowl. Sprinkle yeast over and stir until dissolved.
Add milk, sugar, eggs and butter. Stir.
Add flour, salt and ginger.
Mix well.
Place dough onto floured cloth and knead for 10 minutes.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Place on floured cloth and roll out into a rectangle. Butter surface and sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Roll and slice.
Put on pan that has been sprinkled with butter, brown sugar and cinnamon. Let raise until doubled in size.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese until smooth.
Add milk and sugar.
Mix together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into a crust.
Freeze until firm (2 to 3 hours).
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, water and sugar to a boil.
Pour this over cucumbers, green peppers and onions.
Allow to cool before refrigerating.

title: japanese fruit pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Melt margarine or butter on low heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Remove from heat and add sugar.
In a separate dish, blend together eggs.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients to the chocolate mixture.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white icing
directions: Put all in bowl except milk.
Don't overbeat.
Add milk slowly.

title: vegetable-beef chili
directions: In large pan brown beef.
Add onion, beans, tomatoes, chili, sauce, seasoning, carrots, and string beans.
Add zucchini after 20 minutes.
Add red pepper, powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low heat for an hour.

title: baked brie and sourdough bread
directions: With a bread knife, cut a circle through the top of round loaf about 1-inch from edge.
Gently remove center portion of bread loaf, leaving a bowl-shaped bottom.
Cut removed center portion into 1/2-inch strips.

title: pork and rice bake
directions: Coat large casserole dish with melted margarine.
Place chops in dish
and season with salt and pepper.
Top with soup mix, green pepper and rice.
Combine catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Spread
over rice.
Pour in boiling water and sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat sour cream bread
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature.
Put all ingredients into the bread machine in the order listed.
Select white bread and push "Start".

title: "souper" potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into bite size pieces. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt butter and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with soup mix. Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs and vanilla. Sift the flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add buttermilk. Then add the dry ingredients, alternating with the mashed banana. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: molasses crinkle cookies
directions: Combine sugar, Crisco and egg. Beat.
Add the molasses, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well. Chill for at least 3 hours, then roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Dip into sugar. Spread 3-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake just until set, but not hard.
Bake at 325°.
Test in 12 minutes.

title: roasted garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Place garlic and shallots in a 8-inch square baking pan; drizzle with oil.
Cover with foil and roast 40 minutes, turning shallots occasionally, or until they are tender and golden.
Cool.
Squeeze garlic cloves from skins, place in food processor with roasted shallots and any remaining oil in pan. Process until smooth.
Can be made ahead; cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: date roll sandwiches
directions: Combine sugar and eggs in a large mixing bowl; beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add molasses and melted shortening, beating well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; dredge dates and raisins in 1/3 cup flour mixture to reserve molasses mixture alternately with buttermilk, flour, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in reserved date-raisin mixture.
Pour 1 cup batter into each of 7 well-greased 10 3/4-ounce soup cans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in cans on wire racks.
Remove loaves from cans and cool completely on wire racks.
Cut each loaf into 12 slices.
Spread cream cheese evenly over half of date bread slices; top with remaining slices.
Cut each sandwich in half.
Arrange sandwiches on a serving platter.
Yields 7 dozen sandwiches.

title: pickled mushrooms *
directions: Wash mushrooms in cold water.
Cut stems flush with caps. Drain.
Drop into boiling salted water.
Simmer five minutes. Drain.
Place in bowl.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over mushrooms.
Let stand at least one hour or up to four hours in refrigerator, covered.
Drain marinade and continue refrigerating until served.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Soak potatoes in water for 10 minutes.
Drain and squeeze dry in a kitchen towel.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except for oil.
Mix well.
Pour oil in a large skillet and place over medium heat.

title: twinkie torte
directions: Cut the Twinkies in half lengthwise and line a pan with these. Melt the chocolate chips. Add water and sugar to the melted chips. Separate eggs and add the egg yolks, one at a time, to the chocolate mixture.
Beat the egg whites until stiff and then fold into the chocolate mixture.
Pour over the Twinkies.
Let chill in the refrigerator. Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: italian wings
directions: Set the fryer at 350°.
Put wings and onion in fryer.
Pour the spaghetti sauce and seasoned salt on wings.
Cook the wings until done.
Serve with celery.

title: gracie's snack
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and store in an airtight container. This is a good travel snack.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and crushed pineapple in a large bowl.
Add Cool Whip and stir until mixed.
Add 1 to 2 cups mini marshmallows (really add however many you want).
Refrigerate.

title: corn-green chile casserole
directions: Saute onion and peppers slightly in butter.
Mix cornmeal with milk and mix into all ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake in preheated 350° oven about 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Stir all the ingredients in a saucepan and cook over medium-high heat for 3 to 5 minutes until it forms a ball.
Cool and store in an airtight container (Tupperware, butter tub, Cool Whip tub or a plastic bag).
Fun for kids and easy to clean up.

title: lazy daisy oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Add oats to mixture. Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Do not remove cake from pan.
Add frosting and serve from pan.

title: divine salmon
directions: Pat dry salmon. Should be cleaned and opened for stuffing. Squeeze lemon into fish cavity.
Place on buttered piece of foil. Fill salmon with tomato and onion slices.
Season with salt, pepper, tarragon and parsley. Close foil around fish.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute garlic and diced tomatoes. Remove salmon to serving dish.
Spoon any juice over the fish.
Serve with sauteed tomatoes. Garnish with lemon slices.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: shirley's green beans
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt Milky
Ways
with 1 stick butter.
Remove from fire and let cool.
Cream remaining 2 sticks butter with sugar.
Add beaten eggs
and
cooled
chocolate
mixture.
Sift
flour and baking soda together.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk to the batter,
blending
well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease and dust with
powdered
sugar
3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour mixture in a greased and floured Bundt pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients until dough forms.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: carolyn hawkins' chocolate delight
directions: Mix melted butter, flour and broken pecans together.
Pat into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese, 1 cup of Cool Whip and powdered sugar together good. Spread on top of crust.
Mix vanilla pudding, chocolate pudding and milk until thick; spread on top of cheese mixture.
Use rest of Cool Whip on top.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells, rinse in cold water and set aside.
Mix spinach, eggs, Ricotta, Mozzarella, onion salt, garlic powder and Parmesan. Place 1/2 c. sauce in bottom of pan.
Stuff shells and place in pan.
Pour remaining sauce over shells and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: baked cranberries
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish, lightly greased.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onion in margarine.
Then mix all except 1/2 of the cheese.
Pour into large baking pan; top with remaining cheese and bake at 350°.
Makes 25 servings.

title: party slush
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in freezer-safe containers; freeze, stirring occasionally. Serve diluted with any clear soda pop or juice.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Mix juice and rind with egg yolks, sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Gradually add hot water and oleo.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use whites for meringue; top and brown.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blender pecan pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, salt, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla in blender and blend well.
Add pecans and blend just enough to chop nuts coarsely.
Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until top is lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Good for freezer.

title: peach pecan muffins
directions: To standard muffin mix, add peach pie filling (chop up the peach slices, but use all of the can contents, including the thickening, which makes the muffins moist), nutmeg and nuts.
Mix with enough water to make a stiff dough.
Divide into muffin tins. Will make 12 large muffins or 24 medium muffins.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Mix together vanilla or chocolate wafer crumbs, melted butter and peanuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix until smooth cream cheese, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
After mixing until smooth, fold in Cool Whip. Pour over cooled wafer layer.
Mix chocolate pudding with milk and pour over the previous layer.
Spread Cool Whip on pudding layer; sprinkle nuts on top.
Grate chocolate candy bar or crumbs on top of Cool Whip.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat the first 2 ingredients to dissolve.
Add the buttermilk and mix.
Cool. Whip the Dream Whip or use the Cool Whip and fold in along with the nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit cake roll
directions: Use food processor to chop wafers fine and nuts, not so fine. Put wafers and nuts in large mixing bowl.
Cut cherries.
Add with mixed fruit to wafers and nuts.
Mix well.
Add milk and mix well. (Will be sticky.)
Using your hands, divide into 3 parts.
Put wax paper or plastic wrap on countertop.
Sprinkle 1/3 box of powdered sugar and roll 1 part fruit mixture in sugar to form a long roll. Wrap in the wax paper.
Prepare other 2 parts the same way.
Store in freezer.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: texas beans, ala fislar
directions: Dump all 3 cans of beans into a cake pan 11 x 14-inch or such. Chop onion to taste (I use a medium size onion) but try not to overpower with onion, but be sure to use enough.
In other words, whatever turns you on, put it in.
I use about 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, but if you don't like it too sweet, cut it back to 1 cup. Put in 1/2 to 3/4 cup catsup.
Fry bacon (I use 6 to 8 strips fried crisp and drain on paper towels).
Break them up into small pieces rather than leave them whole to get the bacon flavor throughout the mixture.
Stir this mess up so it is a uniform mixture.
Put it into the oven and bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until it looks like it's done.
I always take samples of each kind of bean in the mixture and sample to be sure they are cooked thoroughly.

title: cheese grits
directions: Stir grits into briskly boiling water.
Reduce heat to simmer & cook for 3 - 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When the mixture is quite thick, remove from heat and add oleo, cheese, and garlic. Preheat oven to 350°.
When the oleo and cheese have melted and the mixture has cooled a bit, add the eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake for about 30 minutes or until firm and golden brown.

title: zucchini corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in melted butter until golden brown.
Beat eggs thoroughly and stir in milk, cornmeal, cream-style corn and salt. Mix in sauteed onion, green pepper and cooked zucchini.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in a moderately slow 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Crumble crisp bacon over the top and sprinkle with Mexican pepper seasoning.
Serves 6.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
In separate saucepan, add tomatoes, soups and 2 cans of water.
Stir over medium heat until blended.
Pour chips into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour ground beef over the chips and then cover with soup mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix well and place in casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° for 45 minutes.
Crumble Ritz crackers and mix them with butter. Spread over top and cook during the last 20 minutes.

title: butter cookies(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Mix well all ingredients in one bowl.
Put into long rolls in Saran Wrap.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar while still warm or dip each cookie in sugar before baking.
Makes 4 dozen or more cookies.

title: spinach pinwheel appetizer
directions: Mix together all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread some mixture on tortillas to within 3/4-inch of edges.
Carefully roll up.
Refrigerate covered or wrapped in plastic wrap overnight. Cut into 1/2-inch slices to serve.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix together and pour Catalina dressing over it just before serving to keep Fritos crisp.

title: cinnamon toast not cooked
directions: Trim edges of bread.
Melt butter in microwave. Spoon melted butter onto bread and spread.
Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture all over. Fold over bread and enjoy!

title: crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: In 3 quart oblong baking dish, place chicken; top with cheese. Stir soup and spread over cheese; top with tomato slices. Combine melted margarine and stuffing; sprinkle over tomatoes. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: goulash soup
directions: Saute onion diced fine in 4 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Add paprika. Cook until bubbly.
Put in bowl and set aside. In same pan, melt 4 tablespoons margarine and cubed beef, which has been floured.
Cook until browned.
Add onion, paprika mixture, beef broth and 1 can water.
Heat to boiling, stirring. Add tomato sauce and 1 can water.
Once again, heat to boiling, add potatoes which have been diced.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer at least 2 to 4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix together.
Put in ice cream freezer.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry jello in hot water.
Do not let congeal, but add the cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple with liquid and chopped pecans, if desired.
Set in refrigerator to congeal.
This congeals quickly.
Lime Jell-O can be used also.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugar and flour. Add crushed pineapple and vanilla.
Put into unbaked pie shells.
Preheat oven to 375° and turn down to 350° when pies go into the oven.
Bake about 30 minutes.

title: veg-all italian sausage soup
directions: In large saucepan, brown sausage bits until light brown.
Push to side.
Add butter and diced onions; cook until transparent. Add cabbage; heat 2 minutes.
Add water; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in Veg-All, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake on 350° for 25 to 35 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and 20 to 30 minutes in jelly roll pan.

title: chicken salad with grapes
directions: Combine the Ranch dressing with the celery salt and salad seasoning.
Mix thoroughly. Drain chicken and shred.
Combine with the dressing. Mix thoroughly. Add water chestnuts and gently toss to coat.
Serve on crackers or use as a stuffing in fresh tomatoes.

title: linguine pasta dish
directions: Cut cucumber,
tomatoes,
green
peppers and onion into small bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients well with hands.

title: deli cole slaw
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Spread 1/8 inch of mixture on flat tortilla.
Roll up as jelly roll.
Chill, slice in 1/2 inch slices.
Makes about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Form small balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until brown.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: Put head of cabbage in boiling water to remove outer leaves. Mix ingredients together and roll in cabbage leaves.
Pour 1 can tomatoes over cabbage rolls.
(Can also add 1 can sauerkraut, if desired.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pastitsio
directions: In a large skillet cook meat, onion, and garlic until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, wine, parsley, oregano, salt and cinnamon.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Gradually stir meat mixture into one of the eggs; set aside.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake and add 1/2 can of coconut in batter.
Bake in cookie sheet pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (no more).
When done, poke holes in cake and pour coconut milk over cake.
Mix Cool Whip and 1/2 can of coconut.
Spread over cake while warm.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender.
Cover and blend on low speed for 3 minutes. Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then sprinkle coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Pie makes its own crust.

title: butternut squash
directions: Cut potatoes for frying (about 6 good ones).
Coat with 1 heaping
tablespoonful of flour.
Fry in deep oil.
Salt to taste.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Boil and flake chicken; mix together with cream cheese, sour cream, peas, onions and seasonings.
Flatten each crescent roll; place by spoonful on each crescent roll and roll large end to small end.
Roll in melted butter, then in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with melted cheese or chicken gravy.

title: toffee squares
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Drop in egg and blend thoroughly.
Add vanilla. Add flour, sifted with the salt, mixing well.
Spread batter evenly in ungreased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Spread at once with melted chocolate and sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Sprinkle crushed Cheese Nips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll into balls (good teaspoonful dough). Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Watch closely.
Take out when lightly brown.
Don't brown too much.

title: chicken dish
directions: In an oblong dish, grease bottom with margarine.
Add 1/2 cup uncooked rice. Shake it so it covers bottom of dish.
Cut up chicken and lay pieces in pan.

title: enchilada casserole(a simple introduction to mexican cookery)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).
Lightly butter a 2-quart casserole.
Crush 1/2 cup of the corn chips and reserve for top. In a medium bowl, combine remaining corn chips, Ready Hamburger Mix, chili, enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.
Pour into prepared casserole.
Bake about 20 minutes, until heated through.
Remove from heat.
Spread sour cream on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and reserved crushed corn chips.
Bake 5 more minutes until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in long pan.

title: red and green pepper relish
directions: Use medium blade of food grinder to cut peppers and onions. Drain juice from vegetables.
Add to vegetables the salt, sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling point and boil gently for 5 minutes. Put into hot, sterilized jars and fill to top immediately.
Makes 4 1/2 pints.

title: spicy hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Spread a thin layer on a tortilla and roll up tightly.
Repeat process. Wrap rolled tortilla in plastic wrap and refrigerate or freeze. Prior to serving, allow rolls to return to room temperature before slicing into 1/3-inch slices.

title: granny hughe's plain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy by using mixer. Add flour, which has been measured and sifted, a little at a time. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Place into a cool oven and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.
(Make sure pan is greased and floured.)

title: fancy chicken log
directions: Beat
together the cheese, A.1. sauce and curry powder. Blend in
the
minced
chicken
and celery.
Mix together the parsley and almonds. Set aside.
Mix cheese, A.1. sauce, curry powder, chicken and celery together and form into logs.
Roll logs in parsley mixture.
Slice and serve on Ritz crackers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and mix.
Cut softened butter into flour mixture until fine.
Add egg, flavorings and milk.
Blend thoroughly.
(May work this with your hands to mix well.)
Refrigerate dough for 2 hours.
Roll dough on floured surface 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Watch closely.

title: pecan balls
directions: Heat oven at 325°.
Combine butter Crisco, 3/4 cup powdered sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Combine flour, oats and salt into mixture.
Round teaspoon of mixture into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes or until bottoms are light golden brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Roll in sugar while warm.
Cool completely on cooling rack.
Re-roll in sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: no cook caramel coconut icing
directions: Combine the sour cream and brown sugar.
Mix well.

Stir in coconut and nuts. Great on German chocolate cake. I like to make the cake in a 9x13 baking pan and then I spoon this icing onto the cooled cake. As it sets, it will thicken and look similar to the traditional German chocolate icing but it's not as rich and creamy.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze water out of spinach.
Combine all ingredients.

title: apple-cheese bake
directions: Toss apples in water and lemon juice.
Place in a lightly-greased baking dish (small oblong to medium Pyrex is best).
Combine flour, sugar and salt; cut in butter until resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle flour mixture over apples.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes before removing from oven; sprinkle cheese cheese on top.
Serve.
Good with meats or anything.

title: chimmies
directions: Fry hamburger, onion, garlic and green pepper.
Drain, stir in green chilies and a pinch of salt and pepper.
Fill tortillas. Fold so ends are closed.
Fry in 1-inch of oil until golden brown.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Discard spices.
Serve warm and garnish each serving with a cinnamon stick, if desired.
Makes 9 cups.

title: grandma woodard's pecan pound cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients well.
Then add the remaining ingredients (eggs one at a time, stirring after each) and cream well.
Mix pecans and raisins with 1 tablespoon flour.
Then add this to the batter mix.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Start the oven out cool with cake.

title: squash medley
directions: Parboil squash about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, except for bread crumbs and butter.
Place in baking dish, alternate squash with filling.
Top with bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, heat wine and juice until mixture boils; turn off.
Add raisins and cinnamon; stir. Cover and let set for 15 minutes.
Core each apple, leaving at least 1/2 inch of bottom intact.
Score around bottom of apple and peel to score line.
Place apples in a glass baking dish so they are not touching.
Stuff with juice soaked raisins; spoon remaining juice evenly over apples.
Put water in dish to cover 1/3 inch.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, soup, milk, and onion.
Cook over low heat until bubbly.
Unroll crescent rolls; flatten - spoon chicken soup mixture in center.
Add grated cheese - roll and place in casserole.
Repeat this process on each crescent roll.
Cover with remaining soup.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Add more grated cheese after taking from oven.
Serves 8.

title: rolanda salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: turkey and carrots in orange sauce
directions: Heat oleo in medium skillet over medium-high heat until melted. Cook turkey in oleo mixture until brown.
Place turkey and carrots in a shallow 2-quart casserole.
Mix brown sugar and cornstarch in a small bowl.
Stir in orange juice, garlic salt, basil and pepper. Pour over turkey and carrots.
Add onion over top.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 1/4 hours or until carrots are done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in an 8 to 12-cup measure cup with handle; microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add peanuts; microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir one time.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda; mix until blended.
Quickly spread on greased cookie sheet. Rest 30 to 40 minutes.
Break into pieces.

title: honey butter
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Combine flour, corn meal and soda in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Pour 1/4 cup batter onto a hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked.
Yields 24 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix together and keep in jars or plastic containers.
Use 1/3 cup of powdered chocolate in 1 cup of hot water.

title: raspberry applesauce jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen berries and applesauce.
Mix until berries are thawed.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or jello mold.
Serve with Miracle Whip and sour cream garnish.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then other ingredients. Roll thin; cut and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: southern skillet chicken creole
directions: Brown chicken in Crisco.
Remove from skillet.
In remaining oil, saute onion, pepper, mushrooms and garlic.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes or until chicken and rice are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn pudding without calories plus
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk, salt and sweetener.
Combine corn with remaining ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Mix well; pour into lightly oiled baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy meat pie
directions: Brown onion and hamburger with chopped garlic; drain.
Mix with the flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Fill pie crust with meat mixture.
Top with the shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together; cool.
Beat eggs with sugar in a large bowl; set aside.
Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add cooled chocolate to this, also 1 cup chopped nuts (optional) and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in two 8 x 8-inch pans.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Combine first four ingredients in medium to heavy saucepan. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute or until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into foil lined 8-inch square or round baking pan.
Sprinkle with additional pecans if desired. Chill until firm.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cook the onion in butter in a saucepan over medium heat until transparent. Add the beef and cook, stirring until beef is light brown. Add the flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup and cook for 5 minutes. Add the sour cream and simmer 15 more minutes. Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 6.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: christmas spread
directions: Put beef through grinder. Place in double boiler with egg, cheese and tomato paste. Cook until mixed. Chill spread. When ready to serve, spread on crackers.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix and pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apricot delight
directions: Mix jello, water (hot and cold), marshmallows, pineapple and bananas together and let chill.
Cook together butter, flour, egg, sugar and pineapple juice.
Let cook, then spread on top of chilled jello.
Beat together cream cheese and Dream Whip as directed. Spread as topping.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use 3 to 4 teaspoons of tea to 1 cup boiling water.

title: cornbread salad(really good)
directions: Mix and bake cornbread according to directions.
Cool and crumble.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in dish.
Cover, chill and serve.

title: tea totalers dandelions
directions: Fill 1 quart measure firmly with fresh dandelion blossoms. Rinse blossoms and cut stem close to flower heads.
Cover blossoms with 2 quarts boiling water and set mixture aside to cool. Combine sugar and 2 cups cold water and bring to a boil to make 3 cups syrup.
Add syrup, lemons and oranges to blossom mixture. Let stand for 3 days.
Strain and serve over cracked ice.
Makes more than 2 quarts non-intoxicating beverage.

title: chicken chablis
directions: Combine eggs, parsley, cheese, milk, garlic powder and pepper and mix.
Place chicken in this marinade and refrigerate for two hours.
Bread each chicken breast and fry in oil.
To the oil remaining from frying, add a little water, wine, salt and pepper, parsley and mushrooms.
Pour this mixture over cooked chicken. Serve.

title: fried rice with chicken
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in wok or large skillet over medium heat.
Add cabbage, snow peas, green onions and garlic.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Remove vegetables.
Reserve.

title: california beef and rice skillet
directions: Brown beef with onion and pepper; drain.
Stir in water, rice and bouillon, bring to a boil and simmer (covered) 20 minutes. Stir in tomato, sprinkle cheese; cover, turn off heat.
Let sit 2 to 3 minutes to melt cheese.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix all together.
Chill half, then spread with 1 pint sour cream.
Pour rest of Jell-O mix over and chill.

title: stuffed green peppers
