directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane. Precook green peppers in boiling water about 5 minutes; drain. Sprinkle inside with salt.
Brown meat and onions; add tomatoes, rice Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Stuff peppers and stand upright in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pie crust (single)
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco until crumbly.
Add water and mix into ball.
Roll and line pie plate.
May double for 2 crust pie. Easy enough for a child to make.

title: erin's delicious tomato pie
directions: Pre-cook piecrust according to directions on package. Cool.
Thickly slice tomatoes.
Slice the onion slightly thinner than the tomatoes.
In a mixing bowl, combine the mayo, cheese, basil, salt, and pepper.

title: chocolate acorn cookies
directions: Stir sugar, vanilla and pecans into melted butter. Sift together flour and add to butter mixture. Form into 42 balls, using 1 teaspoon for each.
Flatten one end by pressing onto greased cookie sheet and pinch top to resemble acorn. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: mary jane's apple crisp
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and place apples in bottom.
In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add unbeaten egg.
Cut or stir in the egg until all is coarse like oatmeal.
Put this over top of the apples.
Melt margarine.
Pour over the flour mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Layer lettuce and fruit in order given, sprinkling orange juice on apples.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over fruit.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate. (Best made night before.)

title: beef burgundy
directions: Coat meat in flour and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Thicken or use beef gravy mix.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: enchiladas de mole
directions: For the sauce, pour the oil that has separated from the contents of the jar into a skillet.
Heat the oil, add the mole paste and briefly fry (2 to 3 minutes) over medium heat.
Slowly add the chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer.
Keep warm for tortilla preparation.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage, seeds, onions and nuts. Break noodles and mix with cabbage mixture.
Sprinkle with sauce, sugar and seasoning. Add vinegar and oil. Mix well.

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients. Pour boiling water over All-Bran; set aside. Cream together sugar and shortening in a 6-quart bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in buttermilk, Bran Buds and soaked All-Bran. Add sifted ingredients; mix well. Fill greased tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until brown. Unused batter can be stored in refrigerator up to 6 weeks. Makes 5 dozen.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter together. After all is melted and mixed thoroughly, gently fold in the Corn Chex cereal.
Mix well until all pieces are coated with chocolate mixture.
Be careful not to break cereal pieces.
Pour powdered sugar into a brown paper grocery bag.
Pour coated cereal into the bag.
Close the bag and shake until all is well coated.
Spread on cookie sheets to cool.
Eat it up!
Mmm good!!

title: microwave fudge
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave dish, stir together sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla.
(It will be stiff.)
Top with butter (sliced).
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth. Blend in nuts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt half the butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix in potatoes. In a medium bowl, combine soup, sour cream, onion and cheese. Pour over potatoes. Combine corn flakes and remaining butter. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
You can use any flavor of cake mix.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together.
This will be very dry.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Shape first mixture into small balls.
Dip into melted chocolate mixture using a fork.
Place on wax paper to dry.
Full recipe makes about 90 balls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pineapple juice. Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix cranberries and sugar.
Set aside.
Add all ingredients to jello.
Chill until set.

title: tutti-fruiti surprises(a substitute for cookies at christmas.)
directions: Beat eggs until foamy in a large bowl. Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in melted oleo. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix into egg mixture.
Mix in dates, nuts and candied fruit. Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan, 8 x 8
x 2-inch. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes until top has a dull crust.
Cut into squares while warm.
Cool, then remove from pan and brush with powdered sugar.
Serves 12.

title: jam tarts
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in cream cheese, maple syrup and lemon juice. Add flour and combine until dough is smooth. Chill overnight.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut into 3-inch rounds.
Make an indentation in the center of each.
Spoon jam into each indentation. Bake on oiled cookie sheets at 450° for 15 minutes. Crust should be golden brown and possibly flaking.
If not, return for additional few minutes.
Makes 12.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Sort and wash the berries, remove stems and caps.
Crush berries to extract 4 cups of juice, combine juice with sugar in a large saucepan and mix well.
Place over high heat and cook, stirring constantly until it comes to a rapid boil.
Boil hard for one minute, again stirring constantly.
Add pectin and bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil one more minute stirring constantly. Remove from heat, skim off the foam with a metal spoon.
Pour jelly quickly into sterilized glasses.
Seal and cool.
Yield about 8 to 9- 1/2 pints.

title: honey baked french toast
directions: Mix milk, eggs, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons honey.
Dip bread in mixture on both sides.
Put into greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining mixture over bread.
Drizzle with melted butter or oleo and remaining 2 tablespoons honey.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes or until golden brown and knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in Pyrex baking dish.
Combine chicken, onion, soup, salad dressing, lemon juice and curry powder; put on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: marshmallow crispies
directions: Melt marshmallows in butter or margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat. When syrupy, remove from heat. Stir in cereal until it is well coated.
Press mixture into a greased pan while still warm. Cut into 25 squares when cool.

title: window cleaner
directions: Pour all ingredients into a gallon jug.
Fill the jug with water.

title: maria's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together by hand in large bowl (except additional ketchup).
Shape into loaf in baking dish.
Top with additional ketchup.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Serves 6.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix and freeze all ingredients, except ginger ale, in plastic milk jugs.
Take out of freezer 4 hours before you serve, add ginger ale.
No ice is needed.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes and cook in boiling salted water to cover 30 minutes or until tender; drain and cool completely.
Peel and cube potatoes; combine potatoes, eggs and celery in large bowl; toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice, salt and pepper in small bowl; stir well.
Pour over potato mixture, tossing gently.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Just before serving, add relish and pimiento.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix everything together real good.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: chicken luau
directions: Dip chicken slices in a 50-50 mixture of flour and cornmeal. Heat 3 tablespoons of liquid oil in wok or large saucepan.
Saute chicken in mashed garlic clove until golden brown.
Drain, but leave oil and breading mixture in wok.
Increase heat and add 2 to 3 tablespoons oil to accommodate prepared vegetables and stir-fry until somewhat softened.
Add 1/2 package crushed Ramen noodles and seasoning pack.

Pour pineapple juice into frying vegetables; add chicken and cook until vegetables are done but still a bit crunchy. To zip up the dish, add hot chopped peppers, chiles or cayenne. Serve over Mahatma yellow saffron rice.

title: apricot slices
directions: Blend together the flour and butter; stir in sour cream. Chill 4 to 6 hours.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Roll each into a rectangle, 12 x 6-inch (approximately).
(It is easier to work with 1 piece of dough at a time, keeping other pieces cold until rolling each one.)
Spread rolled out dough with 1/4 of the apricot jam; sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Roll up the 6-inch side as for jelly roll.
Put on ungreased baking sheet.
Do remaining pieces.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.
While warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
When cool, slice in 1-inch slices.

title: "blonde brownies"
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes in well-greased pan.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with a piece of bacon.
Cover bottom of flat greased baking dish with beef.
Arrange breasts over beef. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight if possible.
When ready, bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.
Serves 8.

title: fancy franks
directions: In small saucepan or skillet, combine the chili sauce, currant jelly, lemon juice and prepared mustard.
Add the cocktail franks and pineapple.
Simmer together 15 minutes.
Served warm with cocktail picks.

title: zucchini and tomato
directions: Melt butter and saute green pepper and onions.
Add zucchini, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart covered casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and bake 10 minutes more.
Melt Cheddar cheese on top and serve.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: On pizza pan, layer the first 4 ingredients in order given. Sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Serve with chips.

title: sunshine cake
directions: Make sheet cake using cake box mix directions.
When done, punch holes in cake.
Mix sugar and pineapple and heat together. Pour this mixture over cake.
Next, mix pudding according to directions and spoon this over cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding and sprinkle coconut to top off.
Refrigerate.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Lay bacon on top. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Make jello according to package directions.
Refrigerate until just soft set.
Using electric mixer, beat soft jello until frothy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add drained fruit cocktail, drained oranges and coconut.
Mix gently.
Fold in marshmallows.
Return to refrigerator to finish setting.

title: aunt dollie's chocolate pie
directions: Cook over low heat until desired thickness.
Put in baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients as you would for any cake.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 300° until done, approximately 25 minutes.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Spray a 2 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick spray.
Debone, skin and cut boiled chicken into small pieces.
Spread evenly over bottom of dish, then sprinkle vegetables and boiled eggs completely over chicken.
Mix broth, soup, salt and pepper together and heat until warm.
Pour into casserole dish over chicken.

title: pancho's dip
directions: Grate cheese.
Boil Ro-Tel and water for 3 minutes.
Add spices.
Pour in blender with cheese and mix until smooth.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: watercress sauce verte
directions: Combine mayonnaise, leaves, lemon juice and seasonings, mixing well.
Chill for 1 hour before serving as sauce for cold or hot fish.
Makes 1 cup.

title: "cherry on top"
directions: Cream together Crisco and cream cheese.
Add sugar, egg and almond extract.
Add flour, salt and soda gradually.
Blend well. Chill overnight.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Stir together the flour, salt, baking soda and oatmeal; mix thoroughly and add to the creamed mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips to the mixture. Bake on prepared baking sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: goulash
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger.
Drain.
Saute in onions and green pepper.
Add mushrooms.
Saute for 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce.
Simmer.
Cook egg noodles until tender.
Drain. Add noodles to hamburger mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and French bread.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Separate the eggs (yolks and whites).
Combine water, egg yolks and chocolate chips in blender; blend until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into chocolate mixture. Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Peel and clean
the potatoes.
Place in a pot and cover with water; bring to
a
boil
and let cook over a medium fire until done.
Remove the potatoes from the water and drain.
In a mixing bowl mash the potatoes well.
Add the butter, flavor, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt, sugar and eggs.
Mix well and gradually add the milk until a smooth custard is made.
A little more or a little less milk may be needed.
Pour in a 9-inch pie pan and bake in a preheated
oven
cook
for
to 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Makes 3 to 5 pies.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix in jar; shake and store in refrigerator.

title: tiki steak
directions: Marinate steak in first 7 ingredients for at least 4 hours. Barbecue or broil 5 minutes on each side for medium done.
Baste with marinade while cooking.

title: apple pineapple spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain, rinse and cool.
Cook and stir eggs, sugar and lemon juice over medium heat until thick.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients and chill thoroughly.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Dump all ingredients in pot and bake at 300° for about 3 hours.

title: vegetable soup(diet)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer until vegetables are done.

title: vinegar pie crust
directions: Cut lard in flour.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: quick macaroni and cheese
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Place a layer of macaroni, then slices of cheese over macaroni; dot with butter.
Repeat twice, ending with cheese and butter.
Pour milk over mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Partially freeze chicken.
Slice lengthwise with the grain, about 1/8-inch thick.
In a small bowl, combine until smooth, egg whites, 2 Tbsp of cornstarch, sugar, salt, Accent, pepper & sherry.
Dredge chicken in flour; shake off excess.
Dip chicken into batter.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Place a few strips of chicken in the oil, being careful not to let the pieces touch; saut for 3-4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove the chicken; drain on paper towels; set aside.
Repeat with remaining chicken. Pour off all but 3 Tbsp oil in skillet.
Rinse, pat dry & slice fresh mushrooms.
Add to oil in skillet; saut for 5 minutes; remove.
Add 1/4 cup of water, stir to loosen particles from the bottom of the skillet.
Combine remaining 1 cup water with remaining Tbsp cornstarch & chicken bouillon cubes.
Add to skillet; bring to the boiling point.
Add snow peas, water chestnuts, reserve chicken & mushrooms.
Heat.
Serve garnished with thinly sliced turnip & radish, if desired.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: red cabbage
directions: In a heavy pot, place 1/4 shredded cabbage, apple, and onion. Note:
Four individual layers will be formed.
Sprinkle each layer with salt, pepper, and sugar.
Repeat layers.
Pour vinegar over completed layers.
Cook slowly, until cabbage is tender and has a glazed look (approx. 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
If needed, add more vinegar and seasoning to taste.
Serve HOT.
In order for the seasonings to permeate the dish, it is better if cooked a day or two before serving.
This dish may be frozen.

title: salmon buns
directions: Remove skin from salmon.
Mix onion, green pepper and 1 1/2 cups mayonnaise.
Pile on top of bun halves.
Place tomato slice on top.
Mix 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Spread over top of tomato slices.
Place under broiler until topping is puffed and brownish.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Place cubed bread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and dry mustard.
Pour over sausage mixture, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Dilute soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: teenage special
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 can milk; pour over meat mixture.
Simmer.
Serve on toasted bread.
Great with pickles and chips.

title: jessie's cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Stir in coconut.
Mix crumbs and baking powder separately.
Add alternately with milk to egg mixture.
Finally, stir in pineapple and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: fluffy omelet
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add water and salt; beat until stiff in bowl.
Add flour and pepper to egg yolks.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Cook on low heat until puffy and lightly browned on bottom.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes, until top feels dry and center springs back when lightly touched.
Fill with jelly, crisp bacon, cheese or ham.

title: laura lee's cherry fantasy
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together for crumbs; press into large cake pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Cool and crumble. Place crumbs in pan, reserving several for topping.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter until it forms soft
ball in water.
Add dates and cook until dates melt some.
Add vanilla, then beat until creamy and add nuts.
Roll into log in wet cloth. Let cool, then cut into slices.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine margarine, Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Mix well.
Pour cereals, nuts and pretzels into a large Ziploc zipper bag.
Pour margarine mixture over cereal mixture inside Ziploc bag.
Seal top of bag securely.
Shake bag until all pieces are evenly coated.
Put in roasting pan.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and store.

title: delicious pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, flour, egg yolks, milk, salt and cinnamon. Cook, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell and serve with whipped cream.

title: cough syrup
directions: Bring to boil.
Let cool until warm.
Give 2 teaspoons as often as needed.

title: simple slaw
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together and cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Let cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss.

title: reuben salad
directions: Toss together and top with Thousand Island dressing.

title: chicken casserole iv
directions: Place breasts in bottom of crock-pot.
Mix other ingredients in bowl.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cook on low all day (8 to 10 hours).
Serve over egg noodles or rice.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin tins.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Refrigerate up to 2 days before serving.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef in pan.
Drain fat. In 13 x 9-inch pan, spread ground beef and onion on bottom.
Put layer of Tater Tots on top.
Mix in a bowl the soup and milk and pour on top of Tater Tots.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: goes on anything barbeque sauce
directions: Saute
onion in 1 teaspoon diet
or
regular
margarine. Add remaining ingredients and cook, simmer 25 minutes, blending well. Pour over chicken
parts, chops, etc.
if baking.
Brush on grilled poultry
or
meat
(for
barbecue)	during	cooking. Recipe is easily increased.
May
be
made	ahead and stored in refrigerator up to 1 week.	May be frozen up to 3 months.
Thaw before using at room temperature.

title: vitality mould(4 to 5 persons)
directions: Wash the spinach thoroughly in several changes of water.
Put into a large saucepan with a very little salt and cook slowly without the addition of any extra water until it is quite tender. Rub through a sieve.
Melt the margarine in a saucepan.
Stir in the sieved spinach.
Season.
Add the herbs, breadcrumbs and beaten eggs.
Blend well and put into a well-greased basin.
Cover with greased paper and steam until the mixture is set and firm, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with white sauce.
(WCB)

title: surfer squares
directions: In large saucepan, over low heat, melt butterscotch chips, brown sugar and butter.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients to make batter.
Dip boiled hot dogs into batter and fry in deep, hot fat.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in butter for 10 minutes.
Blend eggs and cheese; add seasonings.
Stir into vegetables.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish, pressing over bottom and up sides.
Spread dough with Dijon mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, syrup, water and salt in a saucepan over low heat. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to a very hard ball.
Before it reaches this stage, beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour the syrup into the egg whites (beat while pouring).
Do not scrape bottom of pan.
Continue beating until the mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop on a piece of wax paper from a teaspoon.

title: cinnamon candy popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine butter, corn syrup and candies.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over popcorn and mix thoroughly.
Turn into 2 greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and place on waxed paper to cool.
Break apart and store in airtight containers or plastic containers.
Yields 8 quarts.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic, parsley and ground beef; cook 10 minutes or until browned.
In blender container, place 1 can of tomatoes; blend
on high speed 30 seconds or until chopped.
Hand squash the second can of tomatoes.
Add to onion mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, 1 to 3 hours.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: rice patties
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine remaining ingredients, including egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Fry in patties.
Cover with mushroom soup and 1/2 can of canned milk.
Cover and heat until hot.

title: cheese roll #1
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend in lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Put Cheddar cheese, garlic, onion and pecans through food chopper, using fine blade.
Blend mixtures together thoroughly. Cover and chill. Divide mixture into 2 balls or 1 large round ball. Coat one with chili powder or paprika. Roll the other in chopped parsley or pecans.
Chill. Slice thin. Surround with a variety of wafers.

title: fried bananas
directions: Peel bananas and set aside.
Blend remaining ingredients together and add slowly cold water, large beaten egg and coconut milk.
Blend until well mixed.
Heat vegetable oil until smoking and reduce heat slightly.
Dip banana into batter and slide into hot oil carefully.
Cook 2 to 3 bananas at a time and turnover once.
Cook until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan; pour in cocoa until thoroughly mixed.
Put sugar in separate bowl and then pour cocoa over sugar. Mix thoroughly.
Mix vanilla and milk in with sugar mixture.
Mix together well.

title: banana butterscotch pie
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add 1 cup of milk mixed until smooth. Bring to a boil
over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Let boil until smooth and thick, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks with fork into remaining cup of milk and add to first mixture, cooking again until smooth and thick. Remove from heat. Stir in butter and vanilla. Cover and cool.

title: creamy pasta with broccoli
directions: In saucepan, cook fettucini in boiling water, according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, heat oil in a 10-inch skillet, add garlic and saute until golden.
Add Ricotta cheese. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cheese begins to melt and bubbles appear.
Add reserved cooking liquid, salt and pepper; stir to combine.
Drain fettucini well and return to saucepan. Add cheese mixture and broccoli; toss lightly to combine.
Serve each portion sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: In a bowl, mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; stir to dissolve sugar; set aside.
Chop broccoli flowers and stems (use only peeled, tender stems).
Combine broccoli, onions, pecans and raisins.
Pour in the mayo dressing and toss.
Finally, sprinkle bacon bits over all.
Serves 12.

title: squash casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook sliced squash and chopped onions in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine cream of chicken soup and sour cream with carrots; fold in drained squash and onions. Combine stuffing mix and melted butter.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of oblong baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna log
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Shape in log and form on a plate.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place stuffing mix in large baking dish, pour in melted butter and mix.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well; add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour with soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix well; bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Can be dropped by spoonfuls or chilled and rolled.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixing bowl, sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
In another bowl, combine egg and milk.
Beat lightly with fork.
Add to flour mixture all at once, stirring enough to make soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board, knead 15 times.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch rounds.
Place on ungreased baking sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Makes 16 biscuits.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into prepared pie crust. Cover top with crust; crimp edges to seal.
Split top and brush with egg.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: mother's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over meat (about 3 pounds).
Cover and simmer until done.

title: marie's blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line muffin tins with papers.
In a bowl, beat egg with fork. Add oil and dry ingredients. Stir until moist. Batter should be lumpy.
Fill papers 1/2 full of batter. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Best to make dough the day before.
Cream together shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add egg yolk and mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, soda and spices.
Stir in flour mixture and mix well.
Chill.
Roll out 1/3 of dough, 1/4-inch thickness on a floured board.
Keep remaining dough refrigerated. Cut with 5-inch gingerbread cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and decorate with raisins or as desired.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: mocha coffee
directions: Either dry creamer or milk if you want.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat shortening until creamy in mixing bowl.
Add sugar gradually to shortening and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Add flour mixture alternately with bananas using small amount each time.
Turn into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Nuts can be added (about 1/2 cup) to egg mixture.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat juice and dissolve gelatin and add all ingredients.
Pour into oiled molds to congeal.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Add 3 1/4 cups peanuts and food coloring. Cook to a hard boil stage over medium heat.
Remove from heat. Add butter and salt. Beat until thick. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper lined cookie sheet. Cool. Store in airtight container.

title: peanut butter cookies with nuts
directions: Combine butter and sugar; cream together.
Add peanut butter and mix, add egg blend.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt and mix.
Add nuts and mix.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll into one inch balls and press onto cookie sheet with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Serve with Fritos or wheat crackers.

title: key lime "sublime"
directions: Mix the lime and lemon juices together.
Put the juices, Cool Whip and condensed milk in a large bowl.
Mix at medium speed until blended.
Add to crust and refrigerate about 2 hours. Enjoy!

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour one time.
Mix butter, margarine, vanilla and sugar.
Beat in 1 egg at a time while you sift in the flour.
(The batter will be very thick.
You will have to spoon batter into pan.)
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick "no bake" cake
directions: Crumble cake and spread evenly in bottom of an oblong dish or pan.
In saucepan, combine 1/2 cup water, sugar, strawberries, butter and cornstarch.
Cook until mixture has thickened; set aside.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water and add to strawberry mixture.
While still hot, pour over crumbled cake. Place in icebox and let jello mixture chill until firm.
Prepare Dream Whip or use Cool Whip; spread over cake to create frosting effect.
Chill.

title: pucker punch
directions: In a large container, combine pineapple and add juice of your choice and vodka.
Chill.
To serve, pour into punch bowl.
Mix in ginger ale and club soda.
Stir well.
Add frozen ice ring made with 7-Up.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and water in separate bowl and mix until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture and stir in chips and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix sausage and cheese.
Form in small balls.
Stuff mushrooms with balls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Serve hot.

title: supreme caramel sauce
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and butter in saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently, until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking until it forms a firm ball in cold water or 242° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and cream.
Stir to blend.
Cool.
Serve warm over dumplings, cake or apple pie.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and soda.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour liquid over dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Grease and flour large deep cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter easter eggs
directions: Mix together powdered sugar, peanut butter, coffee, margarine and vanilla until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Shape by teaspoonful into egg forms.
Chill in refrigerator for 4 hours. In double boiler, melt chocolate and wax.
Dip eggs into chocolate, one at a time using 2 forks or toothpicks.
Chil until chocolate chills.
(Re-dip into chocolate for a thicker coating, if desired.) Store in refrigerator.

title: fudgy crunch yellow cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In small bowl, combine 1 cup dry cake mix (reserve remaining for cake), 1/2 cup dry frosting mix (reserve remaining for frosting) and 1/3 cup butter.
Stir until crumbly; add nuts.
Press on bottom of prepared pan.
In large bowl, blend remaining dry cake as directed on package.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with remaining frosting mix prepared as directed on package, decreasing water by 1 tablespoon.

title: german potato salad
directions: Slightly brown bacon, drain and put grease back into pan. Combine flour, sugar, vinegar and water into bacon drippings (use large skillet).
Add onions, salt and pepper; simmer until onions are tender.

title: nut cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Chop pecans fine; crush crackers.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour in a greased pie plate. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cover with Cool Whip.

title: seven layer yummies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs; pat into pan.
Add by layers: chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour milk over all ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serves 24 or more.

title: pink lemonade ice cream cake
directions: Slice cake horizontally into 2 layers.
In bowl, combine ice cream and frozen lemonade.
Swirl gently.
Spread 1/2 of ice cream mix on bottom cake layer.
Place second cake layer on top of ice cream.
Top with remaining ice cream.
Freeze 30 minutes.
Garnish with strawberries and mint, if desired.
Calories 258 per serving, 10 gr fat.

title: joyce's ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Place Swiss cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Cook broccoli in microwave 7 minutes using directions on package.
Drain.
Spread over cheese.
Add layer of mushrooms, then ham.
Beat eggs; add milk, flour and salt.
Pour over layered mixture in pie shell. Shred Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli - cheese soup
directions: Combine broccoli, half and half, Velveeta, cream of celery soups, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Cook in crockpot on low for several hours.
Stirring frequently.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all together except brown sugar and nuts. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched or pulls away from side of pan. DO NOT UNDERBAKE. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Spoon hot butter glaze over warm cake.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Boil noodles in salted water until tender.
In separate bowl, mix rest
of
the
ingredients.
Then
mix	in
noodles; spread in greased
pan.
Mix	1/2
cup
corn	flake crumbs and sugar. Sprinkle on
top
of noodles and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well after baking.

title: cream-style corn
directions: In saucepan or skillet, melt butter.
Add 2 tablespoons water and corn.
Cover and cook until tender (approximately 12 minutes). Add
salt,
sugar and flour.
Pour water in 1/2 cup at a time, until desired thickness of cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk and salt to soft ball stage.
Add peanut butter just before removing from fire.
Do not stir!
Cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture is creamy, thick and will hold its shape.
Pour on greased dish.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans. Marinate overnight. Add pecans 1 hour before serving.

title: s o s
directions: Brown ground beef slowly, breaking up in small pieces. Drain off grease and add all ingredients. Simmer. Season to your taste.

title: deer vegetable stew
directions: Cook the deer meat and carrots for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours in enough water to cover well.
Add rest of ingredients and cover with water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in open kettle and add water, depending on the thickness you prefer.

title: sheath cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour; set aside.
Mix together oleo, Crisco, cocoa and water; bring to boil.
Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well.
To this mixture add remaining ingredients. Mix well and pour into large greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: indian rice pilaf
directions: Rinse rice until clear and drain.
Soak saffron in 2 tablespoons of hot water.
In a heavy 3 to 4-quart pan, melt butter.
Add cinnamon and cloves and coat with butter.
Add onions and cook 7 to 8 minutes until soft and golden brown.
Add rice and cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add 4 cups water and bring to boil.
Stir in sugar, molasses, salt, cardamon seed and saffron with its water.
Simmer covered for 25 minutes.
Fluff and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onions in skillet. Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Layer into bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with corn.
Top with mashed potatoes, then Cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, eggs, pickles and salt together. Moisten with mayonnaise or salad dressing.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze until ready to eat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, orange and sugar and let stand overnight. Mix Jell-O and hot water; let sit until partially set.
Mix all ingredients together and let set.

title: greek hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add spices while browning.
Add water and cook until thick.
Serve on hot dogs or hamburgs with raw chopped onion.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and melted margarine together.
Put in bottom of 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Bake for 5 minutes @ 350°, then cool completely.

title: mom's apple pie
directions: Mix the sugar and water and bring to a boil; set aside.
Make dough as though you were making biscuits.
Roll out and place fruit on top and press it into the dough.
Roll up like you would a jelly roll.
Slice.
Place in a baking dish greased with one stick of melted butter.
Pour the sugar and water mixture over this and bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry citrus punch
directions: In large punch bowl, mix all ingredients except ginger ale. Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish with lemon and orange slices.
Makes 144 ounces.

title: gumbo
directions: Simmer chicken, water, onion flakes, bay leaf and salt until tender.
Remove meat from bone; skim fat from broth and reserve. Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil; about 5 minutes without browning.
Add tomatoes, parsley, thyme, cayenne pepper, garlic and broth to onion mixture and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add okra and chicken and simmer 20 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in file powder just before serving.
Cook rice according to package.
Serve in bowl over 1/3 cup hot cooked rice.
Yields 8 servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in frying pan.
Add tomatoes, salt, soup and bell pepper.
Let simmer while cooking noodles.
Add cooked, drained noodles and 1/2 cup of cheese to meat mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle on remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pizza
directions: Mix pizza dough as directed on box.
Spread dough on large pizza pan.
Cover with sauce that comes in box.
Sprinkle cheese from box on sauce.
Place pepperoni, onion, green pepper, mushrooms, bacon and sausage on pizza crust.
Cover with grated Mozzarella.
Place in oven preheated to 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit nut roll
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add the graham crumbs.
Add to candied fruit and nuts. Shape into logs about 3-inches long and roll in coconut. Wrap airtight and store.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Let cool.
Add buttermilk.
Stir until well mixed.
Add Cool Whip. Stir until well mixed.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: corn parmesan chowder
directions: In a large pan, add water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper; cook until done.
Do not drain.

title: cajun chicken vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pot or soup kettle.
Add vegetables, spices and seasonings.
Saute 4 or 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth. Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add tomato juice and V-8 juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and cook until rice is tender, about 20 minutes.
Add chicken and shrimp.
Serve.
Makes 10 cups.

title: shrimp and rice(recipe for diabetics)
directions: Mix everything, except rice and shrimp, in large skillet, stirring occasionally.
Boil gently, uncovered, until celery is nearly tender (about 30 minutes).
Stir in shrimp; boil until shrimp are cooked, but still tender (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Cook rice as directed, omitting margarine or butter.
Serve shrimp on rice.
Yield:
4 servings; 215 calories per serving.

title: crisp sweet relish
directions: Combine ground vegetables in large bowl; sprinkle with salt. Cover with ice cubes.

title: applesauce bran muffins
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix All-Bran, milk, and applesauce together.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil and beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Pour into 12 lined muffin pans.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 2-quart casserole. Cook 7 to 8 minutes on Full power.
Add margarine and vanilla and blend.
Cook for 2 minutes or until it reaches 300°.
Stir in baking soda until light and foamy.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: mock apple rings
directions: Soak the cucumber
rings
in
the lime and 8 1/2 quarts cold water
for 24 hours, stirring the lime frequently.	Drain and rinse well	to
remove
lime.
Soak
in cold water.
Rinse well and drain.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Combine hamburger, onion, salt, pepper and chili powder (season to taste).
Brown well.
Mix together mushroom and celery soups. Layer bottom of dish with package of Doritos.
Then layer with meat and then soup mix.
Pur Ro-Tel over mixture and then top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese bubbles.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: In a skillet, brown the meat and onion; drain any fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart to 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oh so good pie(no cooking required)
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice until smooth.
Add pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Mix.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate several hours prior to serving.

title: basque skillet dinner
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: skillet chicken primavera
directions: Toss chicken in flour, parsley and basil; coat well.
In a large skillet, heat olive oil and garlic.
Add chicken and cook until lightly browned.
Pour in soup, mushrooms, onion and zucchini.
Stir over medium heat until heated through.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add 2 packages frozen strawberries and bananas.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stuffed nasturtiums
directions: Soften the cream cheese with the mayonnaise
Add the remaining ingredients, except the nasturtiums.
Roll this mixture into balls and fit the base into the nasturtium flowers.
Top with a bit of chopped chives or any edible blossom.
Ring the platter with nasturtium leaves or serve as individual salad garnishes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine first 6 ingredients; add next 3 ingredients, beating with electric mixer until combined.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Turn into pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix corn flakes and margarine together.
Put half in bottom of baking dish, 9 x 13-inch; add shredded cabbage.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over cabbage; sprinkle remaining corn flakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blue ribbon pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until like cornmeal.
In a 1 cup measure beat together vinegar and egg, then fill cup with cold water.
Mix together flour and water mixture.
It will be soft and sticky.
Roll out piece of dough on well-floured board to 2 to 3 inches wider than pie pan.
Place in lightly floured pan.
Should make 2 (2 crust, 8-inch) pies.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes.
Add potatoes to boiling water.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain; cool and peel.
Cut potatoes into cubes; combine in bowl with onion.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix with Italian salad dressing.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: pie crust with oil
directions: Put flour and salt in medium bowl.
Combine oil and milk in a cup.
Make a well in the flour; pour oil and milk mixture into well.
Stir until mixed.
Round up dough and divide in half.
Roll out between sheets of waxed paper.
Invert dough in pie pan, then remove waxed paper. If using a double pie crust, invert in the same way.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix sugar and butter, then egg.
Add milk, alternating with flour, baking powder and salt mixture.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix rice, hamburger, salt, pepper and onion.
Form meatballs; put in pan and brown.
Make sure they are browned all the way through.
Drain grease.
Add tomato soup and water.
Cook until hot.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Flake salmon; remove bones.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow candy
directions: Melt the chocolate chips with peanut butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in marshmallows.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable soup for canning and eating
directions: If you use fresh vegetables, cook each separately, then mix together after cooking, then bring to boil.
If canning soup, add potatoes after opening for use or add to the rest of the vegetables if cooking to eat immediately.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients in a pan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan and becomes doughy in consistency. Knead until cool.
Model different colors of clay into different with cookie cutters.

title: overnight cherry salad
directions: Combine cherries with pineapple, marshmallows, coconut, almonds and sour cream.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: salmon pie
directions: Start oven at 325°. Grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine potatoes, cheese and egg yolk. Press mixture in prepared baking dish, covering bottom and sides. Make thick ruffled edge of potato-cheese mixture around top. Cook onions in butter or margarine 5 minutes. Stir in flour smoothly. Add lemon juice and continue to stir to smooth paste. Add milk. Stir and cook until sauce is smooth. Add salt, pepper and pimento. Break drained salmon into large pieces. Add to sauce and pour into potato-lined casserole. Bake about 25 minutes or until potato edge is browned. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vittorio's cannoli filling
directions: Pass
Ricotta cheese through a sieve or strainer, then lightly hand mix with confectioners sugar, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add chocolate and candied fruit.
Refrigerate mixture until ready to fill shells.

title: apple-cinnamon waffles
directions: Combine baking mix, milk, sugar, oil, cinnamon and eggs.
Beat with wire whisk or hand beater until smooth.
Stir in apples. Pour into center of hot waffle iron.
Bake until steaming stops. Top with Apple Cider Syrup.

title: grandmother's tennessee peach cobbler
directions: Melt
oleo
in	2
quart
casserole in 350° oven.
Make batter using flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour into casserole.	Don't
stir.
Place peaches on top of butter evenly; don't
stir.
Bake	at
350° about 1 hour.	Serve hot with milk or whipped cream, if desired.

title: melt in your mouth chicken
directions: Boil together cream of chicken soup with the 2 cups of broth. Mix this with the cut up chicken and pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix the buttermilk, flour, salt, margarine and pepper.
Pour over top of chicken.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 425° oven.
Serve hot.

title: biscuit pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and milk.
Keep stirred on medium heat until it thickens.
Add your leftover biscuits until your pudding is as thick as you like it.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baking pan. Top with egg whites, beat stiff and sweeten.
Brown in oven.
Cool and serve.

title: mama's icing
directions: Cook over low heat until thick.
This is very good with coconut added and poured over a plain cake.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add oil; beat well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, vinegar; beat well.
Add food coloring; mix well.
Bake at 350° in three 8-inch greased and floured round cake pans for 25 minutes.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: danish pastry
directions: Stir yeast in water until dissolved.
Beat in sugar, egg, salt, cardamom and 3 ounces margarine.
Mix with flour and knead until dough is smooth and pliable.
Cover dough and allow to rise to double volume.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and boil sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir up and spoon onto waxed paper.

title: white guacamole
directions: Blend all ingredients, except tortilla chips.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Serve with chips.
Must be prepared ahead.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli cauliflower scallop
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower separately.
Drain and cool. Add flour to 2 tablespoons melted butter and stir over low heat to make a smooth paste but do not brown.
Drain mushrooms.
Mix liquid with milk.
Gradually add to flour/butter mixture.
Cook, stirring frequently until mixture thickens and add cheese.
Season with seasonings.
Add mushrooms.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl and chill for 1 to 2 hours. Form into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Freeze them for 15 minutes and then bag them.
Keep them frozen until you're ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough into an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until browned; cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on top.
In a saucepan, combine the sugar, orange juice, water, lemon juice, cornstarch and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Cool.
Brush over fruit. Chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 9x13 greased and floured pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mud cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Combine pudding and whipped topping.
Stir into cream mixture.
In large flowerpot layer crushed cookies and creamed mixture, beginning and ending with cookie crumbs.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Cream the cheese and combine with pineapple and pineapple juice.
Add nuts and mix with Jell-O mixture.
Pour into 3-quart casserole dish.
Chill overnight.

title: pepper jelly turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour and cheese in food processor. Add butter and pulse until coarse crumbs.
Add water and process until mixture holds together.
Divide dough in half.
Roll between wax paper to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into circles (2-inch) with biscuit cutter.
Transfer to ungreased cookie sheet.
Spoon 1/4 teaspoon pepper jelly and 1/4 teaspoon ham into center of dough. Fold over and seal edges with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Good for freezer.
To reheat, bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
If dough is sticky, refrigerate on cookie sheets for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crushed Ritz crackers (1 tube) and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian meat balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly. Shape meat mixture into 30 balls.
Roll in flour and brown in shortening.
Drain excess fat.
Prepare Sweet-Sour Sauce.
Pour over meat balls and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Melt butter in boiling water.
Add flour and salt all at once; stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until smooth.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together. Will keep about 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: praline yams
directions: Place yams in serving dish; keep hot.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Heat, stirring constantly for 5 minutes. Pour over yams; serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: country style corn
directions: In heavy saucepan, fry bacon pieces until crisp. Add other ingredients, except corn. Bring to rolling boil. Add corn and cook on high until corn thaws. Thicken immediately with small amount of cornstarch.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Cut up chicken into bite size pieces.
Peel and slice the carrots.
Cover bottom of skillet with oil; saute chicken until tan.
Add carrots; cover with water and cook until soft (about 1/2 hour).
Stir in sweet 'n sour sauce; simmer.
Let thicken while cooking rice according to package.
Stir in drained pineapple. Serve over rice.

title: bavarian mints
directions: Melt chocolate and butter into mixing bowl.
Add condensed milk.
With electric mixer beat on low 1 minute; beat on high 1 minute.
Refrigerate 15 minutes but take out every 5 minutes and beat by hand.
After 15 minutes beat on high 1 minute.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate.
Cut into 1/2-inch squares when set.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: lentil soup
directions: Remove the rind of Doubt;

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Put in order listed.
Spread Miracle Whip over top of peas, then cheese and bacon bits.
Best if sits overnight.

title: grandma rose's apple fritters
directions: Mix flour, eggs, milk, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Add diced apples.

title: corn muffins
directions: Add sugar to cornmeal and stir.
Combine eggs, water and shortening.
Pour 1/2 liquid into mix; blend.
Add rest of liquid and beat.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil in mixing bowl; add eggs 1 at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Add vanilla and walnut flavoring, carrots and chopped nuts and flour.
Pour into well greased tube pan; bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° (do not open oven door as cake will fall). For best results, measure flour first, then sift 3 times.

title: whole wheat muffins(low-fat)
directions: Contains 120 calories/serving (kcal), 5 g fat/serving, 3% calories from fat, 1 mg cholesterol, 4 g protein and 144 mg sodium.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Pour 1/2 cup buttermilk in bowl.
Tip chicken in milk and roll in flour with salt and pepper.
Melt butter in casserole dish. Put breast side down.
Bake 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Turn over and bake 15 minutes.
Turn chicken back to breast side down and mix 1 cup buttermilk and mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems.
Brush caps with melted butter. Combine butter and garlic.
Add cheese and mix well.
Add wine, soy sauce and cracker crumbs. Fill caps with mixture.
Place on foil covered sheet and broil 3 minutes.

title: thermos flask lunch
directions: Briefly saute the spices in the ghee.
Add the mung bean dahl, rice and chopped vegetables.
Cover with the water and simmer for 5 minutes.
While still boiling hot, quickly pour the mixture into a one-liter or one-quart thermos.
Close the thermos quickly and leave it closed for about 4 hours.
The meal will cook and be ready to eat after 4 hours in the thermos.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish (9 x 13-inch pan).
Top with layer of cheese and crumbled crackers.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain the
oil from 1 jar of artichokes into a skillet. Saute the onion
and
garlic
in the oil.
Drain the other jar and chop all
artichokes.
In
a bowl, beat the eggs, then add bread crumbs,
Tabasco, oregano, salt and pepper.
Stir in the onion, garlic,
cheese and artichokes.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan
for
hour
at
Cut into squares and serve hot. These
squares
can
be
made
in advance and then rewarmed on a cookie sheet.
Makes about 30 squares.

title: sorghum syrup pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend syrup, milk, butter, flour and salt.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add beaten whites.
Pour into an unbaked pastry and bake 40 to 50 minutes or until set; test with pie tester.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix flour, cheese, baking powder and seasoning in a bowl.
Add beaten egg.
Mix. Add enough milk to make a stiff dough.
Pinch off a small piece of dough and on a flat surface, roll with your hands into a straw, about 1/2-inch thick and 4 or 5-inches long.
If the ends are pointy, cut ends off and return to dough.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.

title: roll recipe
directions: Scald milk.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Allow to cool.
Add water, eggs, yeast and flour, 1 quart at a time.
Knead; allow to rise to double in size.
Push down; allow to rise again.

title: pastry for pies
directions: Measure flour and salt in bowl; cut in shortening.
Sprinkle with water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until flour is moistened and dough is clean from sides of bowl.
Roll into ball and flatten round with rolling pin on lightly floured surface.
Makes 2 (8 or 9-inch) pie shells.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave bowl, stir together the sugar and syrup.
Microwave 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes, until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla; blend well. Microwave 1 to 2 minutes.
The peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot!
Add soda and gently stir until foamy.
Pour mixture into lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco and add eggs 1 at a time.
Add the rest.
Mix with hands.
Grease cooker and pinch off mixture.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 320°.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: sauteed broccoli rabe
directions: Rinse off broccoli rabe; drain well.
Steam broccoli rabe in a covered pot or microwave on High for about 5 to 8 minutes.
Cover the bottom of a deep sided frypan or Dutch oven with about 1/8 inch of olive oil.
Cut garlic cloves into slivers.
When oil is warm, add garlic; saute until transparent.
Carefully add broccoli rabe (it may splatter when first put in pan).
Add crushed red pepper to taste; saute for about 8 minutes.
Recipe will serve 4 persons as a side dish.
Can also be served over linguini as a main dish.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar and flour.
Press into 10 x 14-inch greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Beat eggs slightly and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over pastry.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.
Cut into squares.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, lard, egg and water.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture, then blend in oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate kahlua trifle
directions: Bake cake per package directions. When cake has cooled completely, prepare pudding per package directions.
In a clear footed bowl (trifle dish), crumble 1/3 of the cake into pieces. Sprinkle Kahlua on the crumbled pieces.
Spread layer of pudding onto Kahlua and cake. Spread layer of Cool Whip onto pudding layer.
Repeat 2 more times, ending with Cool Whip layer on top. Finish off with a cherry on top.

title: buttermilk rolls(servings:  8)
directions: Dissolve yeast in the lukewarm water; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar in mixer.
Add eggs one at a time until well blended. Add buttermilk, yeast mixture and salt.
Mix well.
Mix baking powder with 1 cup flour; add to mixture and blend well.
Add remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Knead until satiny.
Let rise in greased bowl (covered) until double in bulk.
Shape; let rise until light.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook first three ingredients in boiling water and until tender; drain.
Stir in cheese and Miracle Whip.
Pour into a baking dish, crumble Ritz crackers over the top.
Pour over 1/4 cup melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Put rest in and stir.
Pour in unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: autumn vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in large saucepan.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: nut ball cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll balls in powdered sugar while hot.
Let cool and roll in powdered sugar again.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix by hand the Bisquick mix, cheese and sausage.
Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown on all sides.

title: hot crab salad sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients; split buns, butter and fill with salad. Wrap in foil and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: money bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with a pinch of salt.
Set aside. Mix 2 cups flour, sugar and 1 teaspoon salt; sift well.
Add butter, mix well; add eggs and the rest of the flour.
Mix well. Cover, let rise 1/2 hour or until double in size.
Roll dough on floured board.
Cut out dough 1/2-inch thick in circles.
Baste in reserved butter on both sides.
Place flat in Bundt pan, pieces overlapping each other.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles per package directions; drain.
Combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion and salt.
Blend celery soup and milk.
Add shredded cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts. Add to noodle mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle lightly with cheese.
Top with slivered almonds or broken potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 425°.

title: sally's washboard cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat smooth and add eggs; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Set aside small amount in which to dredge raisins.
Add dry ingredients to other mixture, then raisins, flavorings and nuts.
Mix well and shape into small balls.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly in a crock-pot and cook.
Add wieners. Serve hot.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in 10-inch skillet over hot coals or on stove until light brown; drain.
Stir in potatoes, onion, salt and bouillon.
Add liquid from tomatoes and beans to skillet.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and beans.
Break up tomatoes with fork; cover and simmer until potatoes are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: summer salad
directions: Cook macaroni; toss with remaining ingredients.
Serve with any dressing.
Nice when served with crackers and fresh fruit.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Marshmallow Creme. Mix until blended. Serve with fresh fruit and cookies as dippers. May also be served as a sauce over fresh fruit or cake. Makes 2 cups.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with salt, pepper and garlic powder in large skillet.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce and simmer while cooking noodles by package directions.
When noodles are almost ready, add sour cream, cottage cheese and chopped onions to meat mixture.
Stir until well mixed.
Grease a large shallow 3-quart casserole with butter.
Place a layer of noodles in bottom.
Sprinkle with olives, mushrooms and about one-third of meat mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until sauce is melted.
Makes 6 to 8 generous servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken until tender.
Cool and cut into small pieces.
Use broth from chicken to prepare dressing as directed on package.
Spoon stuffing into greased baking dish and place chicken on top.
Add vegetables on top of chicken.
Add 1/2 can of water to soup and pour over vegetables.
Place in oven and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini sausage crescent quiche
directions: Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 9-inch quiche or pie pan.
Press over bottom to make crust.
In a large frypan brown sausage, onion and green pepper. Drain.
Stir in zucchini, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, salt, thyme, mushrooms and eggs.
Pour filling into crescent crust.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: layered coconut pecan squares
directions: Mix flour with 1/3 cup of the nuts and the butter; press into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool. Toast remaining pecans and 1/3 cup of coconut on baking sheet at 325° for about 5 minutes.
Beat cream cheese; blend in 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix.
Beat slowly until blended, about 2 minutes.
Add remaining coconut; pour over baked crust.
Spread whipped topping over pudding.
Top with toasted coconut and pecans.
Chill about 2 hours.
Makes 9 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese and spread at room temperature to mix. When all mixed together, let stand in refrigerator overnight before forming into a ball.

title: orange cocoa cake with orange buttercream frosting
directions: Grease 3 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans; line with wax paper and set aside.
Stir together cocoa and boiling water in bowl until smooth; set aside.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar, salt and vanilla in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda into 1 cup buttermilk; add alternately with flour to cream mixture.
Measure 1 2/3 cups batter into small bowl.
Stir in 3 tablespoons buttermilk, 1/8 teaspoon baking soda, orange peel and orange extract.
Pour into one prepared pan.
Blend cocoa mixture into remaining batter. Divide evenly into other two pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely. Using a chocolate layer first, spread with Orange Buttercream Frosting.
Top with orange layer and spread with frosting.
Top with chocolate layer and spread entire cake with frosting.

title: nut brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Add cocoa, flour, vanilla, nuts and salt.
Pour in shallow pan and bake 20 minutes in moderate oven (about 350°).
Will be about 1 inch thick.

title: chicken tortilla soup(serves 4; may double)
directions: Cut chicken in 1/2-inch pieces; cook in large pot for 3 minutes. Add onions, garlic and spices. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Add broth, chilies and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer (add rice), 10 to 15 minutes. Cut tortillas into 1/2-inch strips. Bake 7 to 8 minutes until crisp.
Snip cilantro.
Divide strips into 4 bowls; ladle soup over strips. Sprinkle cheese and cilantro on top. Garnish with lime slices or squeeze juice into soup, if desired.

title: corn oysters
directions: Scrape the
corn from cob.
Sift flour and salt and mix with the egg
and milk.	Stir the corn into batter and drop by spoonfuls into
a frying pan containing melted butter, heated. When brown on one side, turn and cook other side.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos with rolling pin.
In a medium bowl, cream the butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix pudding and milk until thickened.
Fold in Cool Whip, then mix in cream cheese mixture until smooth.
Line a clean, new flowerpot with foil.
Layer cookies, then filling, making sure to end up with cookies on top and add gummy worms and silk flowers!

title: pizza bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Cook and stir sausage and hamburger, onion, pepper and seasoning until brown; drain.
Stir in sauce and 2 tablespoons Bisquick.
Simmer and stir 1 minute.
Pour into pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat 1 cup Bisquick, 1 cup milk and 2 eggs.
Pour over cheese.
Bake until golden, about 30 minutes.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a covered casserole. Make sure lid is tight. Cook in oven at 250 degrees for 5 hours.

title: tiny pigs-in-blankets
directions: Unwrap triangle-shaped crescent rolls.
Cut each triangle into 3.
Wrap around sausages and bake as directed.
These can be made in advance and reheated.

title: honey nut squash
directions: In shallow, microwave-safe dish, microwave acorn squash according to microwave manufacturer's directions.
Halve lengthwise and remove seeds.
Combine honey, walnuts, raisins, butter or margarine and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into squash in dish.
Microwave at High (100%) for 30 seconds or until thoroughly heated and lightly glazed.
Makes 2 servings.

title: veal piccate
directions: Pound veal into thin slices 3 x 3 inches.
Coat with flour. Shake off excess.
Heat 2 teaspoons butter at a time.
Saute veal very quickly.
Keep warm.
Add chicken broth, wine, salt and lemon juice to skillet.
Use a wooden spoon to scrape pan.
Coo 1 minute. Return veal.
Cover and heat 2 to 3 minutes until bubbly.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Arrange veal on platter.
Pour wine over it and garnish with lemon slices.

title: talorine
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Boil noodles while beef cooks.
Drain noodles.
Put meat mixture, noodles, corn, cheese, soup, Ro-Tel and 1/2 can water in large casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.
Bake 1 or 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Recipe can be halved, if desired.
Bake 45 minutes for half.

title: three-vegetable gratin
directions: Boil a large pot of salted water.
Slice vegetables to 1/8-inch thick, keeping separate.
Boil potatoes 5 minutes. Remove with slotted spoon to colander to cool.
Repeat with parsnips, boiling 6 minutes.
Repeat with squash, boiling 2 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in an oblong cake tin.
Mix well until all of the lumps are gone.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Remove skin from chicken pieces.
Place chicken, water, salt and pepper in Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth. Skim fat from broth; strain broth and reserve.
Cook pork sausage in Dutch oven until brown; drain fat reserving 1 tablespoon in Dutch oven.
Add chicken; stir in broth and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring once or twice; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until thickest pieces of chicken are done and rice is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cut in small pieces.
Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Arrange broccoli in 11 x 7 baking dish.
Place chicken on broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and cheese, then pour over chicken.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine
flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening
and mix with hands until it feels like coarse meal.
Add yeast
which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup of very warm water. Then add buttermilk and mix well until all dry ingredients are absorbed. Cut
off
desired
amount
of
dough and shape into biscuits. Bake
in
preheated
oven
for about 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Serve with butter.

title: fig cake
directions: Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Combine and blend all ingredients, except the ham.
Spread the mixture on ham slices.
Roll each piece of ham, starting with lengthwise edge.
Fasten with approximately six or eight toothpicks.
Chill.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Saute onion in butter in large pan. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger
in skillet;
drain grease.
In another pan, heat refried beans	so
it will be spreadable.
In casserole dish, crush half	of corn chips to evenly cover bottom of the pan. Spread half
of
refried
beans over the corn chips; continue to layer
ingredients	with
half
of hamburger, sour cream, cheese and picante sauce.	Repeat layers with remaining corn chips, beans,
hamburger,	sour
cream, cheese and salsa. Cook in 350° oven for
about 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted.

title: that pink stuff
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Stir together well.
Fold in pecans and Cool Whip.

title: crisis casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake covered for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: blackberry jam cake with caramel icing
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each one is added.
Stir in buttermilk and preserves, mixing well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mix.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Test with toothpick.)
Cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain well.
Add all ingredients except crackers and margarine.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake 20 minutes or until brown and crusty at 350°.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break bread in small pieces and moisten with milk.
Mix in rest of the ingredients.
Shape into cakes.
Fry quickly, until brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Cover ingredients with dressing.
Spread over the top. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Seal tight and refrigerate 24 hours ahead.
When ready to serve, mix well.

title: apple strudel
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients with 1/2 cup bread crumbs; set aside.
Cut 2 (25-inch) lengths of wax paper.
Overlap long sides and tape.
On wax paper, place 1 sheet of phyllo.
Brush with butter, then sprinkle 1 tablespoon bread crumbs.
Layer phyllo sheets to make an 18-inch square, repeating each layer with butter and crumbs.
When square is complete, spread the layered phyllo dough with apple mixture.
Roll up as for a jelly roll.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add flavoring.
In a large pan mix flour, cherries, coconut, pecans and walnuts.
(Two measuring cups rounded equals 1/2 pound of walnuts or pecans.)
Pour creamed butter mixture over the flour and mix thoroughly.
Pour in tube or Bundt pan that's been greased and floured and bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Cool; wrap in tinfoil and store in cool place.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash; add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: guamanian chicken-on-a-stick
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, for marinade. Marinate chicken strips for at least 2 hours.
Put 2 to 3 pieces of chicken on a bamboo stick.
Grill over hot coals until well done.

title: great new way to bake a turkey
directions: Salt and pepper inside and out.
Place in a roaster or turkey pan with water.
Tightly cover with lid or heavy-duty foil.
Bake in 500° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and DO NOT OPEN THE DOOR FOR 12 HOURS.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend until well mixed.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with your hands.
Place this mixture in a jelly roll pan, using rolling pin to flatten.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Spread on top of mixture.
Refrigerate until chocolate hardens.
Remove and cut into squares.
Do not put back in refrigerator.

title: great 'n easy granola
directions: Heat oats in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Take out.
Add the rest, pouring honey on last.
Bake until golden brown, stirring about every 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add white raisins when cool.

title: casserole cookies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add rest of ingredients.
Turn into an ungreased casserole; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While hot, stir into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Reroll after they are cool.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Combine these ingredients and mix.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Mix 2 cups of crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake about 5 minutes more or until topping is crunchy.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Line a greased casserole dish with beans.
Top with half of mushroom soup and 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Add another layer of beans, then the remaining soup and margarine. Top with onion rings.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce puffs
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar and cinnamon.
Add applesauce, milk, egg and oil; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Fill muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
