Cool slightly.
Remove; dip in melted butter and roll in Bisquick, cinnamon and sugar mixture.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in an airtight container.
Stir in 3 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: grape salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a glass salad or serving bowl.
Mix gently before serving.
Very simple but delicious.

title: great bean dip
directions: Mix all. Cover and chill in refrigerator for 3 to 24 hours. Serve with tortilla or corn chips for dipping. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix everything except the
bananas. Slice the bananas when it's serving time or mix them in Fruit-Fresh.
They have a tendency to turn dark.
Mix the pineapple juice and mandarin orange juice in a small saucepan. Mix 2 or 3 tablespoons cornstarch in as small amount of water as possible. Add 2 tablespoons sugar or substitute.
Bring to a boil. Cool and pour over fruits.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into pie shells evenly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients (like pie crust).
Add yeast and buttermilk and beat until smooth. Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick, cut with biscuit cutter.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Butter and flour a 12 inch bundt pan.
Mix yellow cake mix and the vanilla pudding.
Add other ingredients and beat 5 minutes or until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in 1/2 bar grated chocolate and add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 40 minutes. While warm sprinkle on some grated chocolate.
After cake cools, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sausage balls
directions: Work cheese and sausage with hand until well mixed. Add flour and milk. Mix well. Make into small balls. Bake at 350 to 375 degrees until done.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add the pineapple and mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt and mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: In kettle, cook bacon until crisp.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add carrots, celery and parsley. Cook 5 minutes longer, stirring once in awhile.
Add tomatoes and liquid. Add spices and bring to a boil.
Mash the potatoes and add water to make 2 quarts of liquid.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook an additional 20 minutes. Add diced clams and juice.
Replace cover and steep for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: candy cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in pan.
After mixture reaches a boil (medium heat), cook 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Drop on cookie sheet or wax paper.
Cool.
Serves 24.

title: edith's boiled custard
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over beaten yolks.
Mix in sugar and flour; boil until thick.
Strain cold whipping cream.
Add to custard. Add vanilla.
Stir and serve chilled.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix wet ingredients, then add well combined dry ingredients. Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Stir once.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together, use 1/2 cup measure per 2 cups hot water.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on package.
Grease and flour two 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dishes.
Divide batter in half and bake in 2 dishes.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Crust will be about 1-inch thick.
While cake is baking, mix in pan:
evaporated milk, 1 cup sugar and bring to rapid boil; remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved and add coconut.
Pour this mixture over the two cakes.
In another pan, mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and oleo.
Heat to a rapid boil and remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until dissolved or melted.
Then add pecans.
Drizzle chocolate mixture over other mixture already on the cakes.
Try not to spread it, as you will get it mixed with coconut layer and it won't look as good.

title: mini applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 36 (1 3/4-inch) muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large bowl, mix wheat germ, oats, flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
In medium bowl, mix applesauce, corn oil spread, egg substitute and vanilla until blended.
With wooden spoon, stir applesauce mixture into flour just until flour is moistened.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream together 2 sticks butter and confectioners sugar; add the cocoa, vanilla and 3 tablespoons butter.
Add 1 whole egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add second egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add third egg and beat 5 minutes.
Put in crust and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chocolate covered pretzels or white almond bark
directions: Melt down chocolate or white almond bark.
Dip whole pretzels in melted bark and place on wax paper until set.
Store in cool area.
Chocolate covered pretzels keep well in airtight container or tin.
Any flavor of cooking bark may be used for variation.

title: banana all-bran nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and All-Bran.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Add to first mixture.
Combine water with bananas and add vanilla.
Pour in greased loaf tin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onion slices about 3 minutes in small amount of water.
Drain.
Place half of vegetables in buttered casserole. Mix grated cheese and soda cracker crumbs.
Pour half cheese mixture over half of vegetables.
Put second half zucchini mix into casserole and cover with remaining cheese mixture.
Mix with stirred egg.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Simmer for 4 hours.

title: chili eggs
directions: Remove seeds from chiles and lay them flat in a well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Whip the eggs until foamy and combine with cheeses; pour over the chiles.

title: roast in mustard
directions: Put a heavy layer of salt and mustard all over roast.
Cook on grate close to coals.
Turn carefully.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 hours.
If crust starts to fall off, set on piece of foil to finish cooking.
When done, break off crust and slice.

title: peanut butter refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter
and shortening together.
Add cake mix and milk.
Beat
until
blended.
Form
dough
into 2 inch roll. Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Slice 1/8 inch thick. Bake
on ungreased baking sheet in hot oven (400°) for 8
to
10 minutes
or until done.
Cool cookies a few minutes before removing
from baking sheet.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Bake pie crust at 350° for 15 minutes. Blend all other ingredients together, except for cherries.
Spread over crust and bake 10 minutes.
Let chill, then put cherries on top.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking for 5 minutes without stirring.
Heat low until just boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Heat the oil and cubed stew meat and brown.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, paprika, sugar, vinegar, molasses and salt plus 1 cup water, and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add more water, if needed.
Add the carrots, onions and green pepper and cook another 30 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until tender.
(Easy Tip:
Freeze cabbage a couple of days; thaw 1 day until limp.)
Remove tough skin on salt pork and grind fat.
Chop and saute onions and salt pork.
Let cool.
Mix ground pork, ground beef, cooked rice and onion and salt pork mixture.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend marshmallow and cream cheese until smooth.
Serve with strawberries, apples and bananas.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs together.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Add apples and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: dixie's southern corn
directions: Microwave cream cheese and butter together. Add corn and chopped peppers. Heat in microwave until bubbly and creamy.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli 3 minutes and drain.
Combine mayonnaise, soup and lemon juice.
Alternate layers of broccoli and chicken in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt matt snyder's persimmon pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Mix it and the butter into corn.
Beat eggs well.
Pour into milk, then stir into corn mixture.
Pour into a 3-quart greased casserole.
At this point, it may be refrigerated overnight or frozen for several weeks.
(If you are freezing, use a dish that is freezer and oven-safe.)

title: shrimp vegetable salad
directions: Combine cooked rice, green peas, mushrooms, celery and olives. Mix mayonnaise and chill. Just before serving, add the chilled shrimp. Serve on leaf lettuce and garnish with tomatoes and olives. Serves 20.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Simmer beef, onion and pepper until done.
Have noodles cooked.
Add tomato soup and corn.
Mix and place in casserole. Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: shrimp capri
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tail portion; devein.
Rinse and pat dry. Place in large ovenproof pan.
Saute garlic in butter in skillet for 3 minutes.
Pour over shrimp.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Broil 3 inches from heat source for 5 to 7 minutes or until done to taste.
Yield:
3 servings.

title: fondue!  fondue!
directions: Melt cream cheese with white wine.
Add Swiss cheese, milk, Worcestershire sauce and parsley.
After this all blends thoroughly add crab meat.
Stir constantly.
I recommend you do this in a double boiler and transfer to a fondue pot later.
Both pots must be wiped with garlic.
Serve with apples and bread cubes to dip.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening; gradually beat in sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill dough, then form into 1-inch balls.
Roll into mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten them with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: old fashioned strip dumplings
directions: Mix eggs, cool broth and salt.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour and stir to make sticky ball.
Turn ball onto floured board and work into least possible flour to keep dough from sticking.
Roll as thin as possible (if thicker, must cook longer).
Cut into 1 1/2-inch strips with a knife.

title: apricot snack loaf
directions: Soak dried apricots in warm water for 15 minutes.
Drain; cut into pieces.
Sift flour and measure.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream shortening and sugar well. Blend in egg; beat well.
Add water and orange juice; mix well. Blend in dry ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Fold in walnuts and cut up apricots.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Push batter up into corners of pan, leaving the center slightly hollowed.
For well rounded loaf, allow to stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 60 to 65 minutes, or until done.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.
Wrap in aluminum foil and keeps well in refrigerator.

title: hugo hot flash's german pizza
directions: Melt fat in a large skillet.
Pare and slice the potatoes. Spread 1/2 of potatoes in the skillet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange 1/2 the Spam strips over the potatoes in spoke fashion.
Add another layer of potatoes, the onion, green pepper and Spam strips.
Cover and cook over low heat for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Beat the eggs with a small amount of milk.
Pour the eggs over all.
Cover and cook until the eggs are set, about 10 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Cover and cook until the cheese melts. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Mix cereal, marshmallows and nuts in large bowl.
Melt white chocolate in double boiler or microwave and pour over cereal mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Push together to make more compact if necessary.
Allow to dry.
(If mixture hardens while working, put back in microwave.)

title: almond nut crackers
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (caramelize).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and immediately pour over crackers that have been placed on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 - 12 minutes or until a little brown.
Remove immediately.
Place on cooling rack.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at joints and discard tips.
Place in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Bake at 375° in another pan 30 minutes.
Retain sauce to baste.
Also good for boneless chicken breast.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Add 1 cup jam to this mixture; alternately sift in dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Bake in two large cake pans or a tube pan in a 350° oven about 1 hour.
Blackberry or strawberry jam is used by this cook.

title: triple twirl alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain. Meanwhile, in small saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Gradually stir in 3/4 cup of Parmesan cheese, then whipping cream until well blended.
Continue heating sauce, stirring constantly, just to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in parsley.
Toss sauce with hot pasta.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Combine crumbs, sugar, margarine and extract.
Mix well.
Reserve 1/4 cup crumbs for topping.
Press remainder into bottom of greased pie pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Beat together sour cream, dip, egg and soups.
Stir in all the Swiss cheese and 1/2 the cheddar cheese.
Stir in potatoes. Spray large casserole dish with Pam.
Pour potatoes in and press down with back of spoon.
Sprinkle remainder of cheddar cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.

title: water yeast bread
directions: Note:
This makes one loaf.
Increase according to desired number of loaves.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix in blender and store in refrigerator.

title: reah bates' orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and shape into meat balls.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, in a 350° oven.

title: blueberry bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until fluffy. Add 2 egg yolks, lemon rind and vanilla.
Beat.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour with the blueberries.
Sift remaining flour and baking powder.
Add flour, alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat the egg whites.
Stir in 1/3 of egg whites.
Fold in remaining egg whites.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into loaf pan.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick is clean.

title: nutt house buttermilk pie
directions: Combine together margarine and sugar; mix in eggs and flour. Beat until fluffy.
Fold in buttermilk and nutmeg (or other flavoring).
Pour mixture in pie shell and bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Flatten sugar dough in a pizza pan and bake as directed.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over cooled crust. (Refrigerate 1 hour.)
Arrange fruit on top.

title: old fashion apple jacks
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup and add milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to dough mixture.
Chill 1 hour before rolling out.
Roll 1/2 dough and place in 9 x 13 cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with corn flakes, then layer with apples.
Dot with butter.
Mix 1 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples. Roll out remaining dough and cover apples.
Beat egg white until foamy and brush over top crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove from oven and drizzle with icing.

title: irish whole wheat soda bread
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together thoroughly, then add enough buttermilk to make a soft dough, similar to biscuit dough, but firm enough to hold shape.

title: oven cheese fondue
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Remove crusts from bread; cut into cubes. Beat eggs, milk and seasonings with rotary beater.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and onion.
Pour into ungreased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or until center is set.
Serve immediately.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Make a thickening of 3 scant cups clear-jel.
Add to mixture; cook until thick.
Cold pack 5 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Soften butter and cheese; mix well with mixer.
Add flour and red pepper.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: boogar hollow biscuits
directions: Whip all ingredients together until nice and smooth.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake in a 400° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Beat egg; blend in undiluted soups.
Add bread cubes and cooked chicken, shredded in pieces.
Do not add salt.
Pour in buttered casserole (6 x 10 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch) pan.
Top with cracker crumbs which have been stirred in melted butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sourdough bread
directions: After you have mixed and kneaded, place in a large greased bowl and let rise most of the day, then punch down and divide into 3 parts and shape into loaves.
Place in greased pans and let rise overnight.
The next morning, preheat oven to 375° and let bake 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350°.
Bake until done (usually 25 to 30 minutes).
Turn out on racks to cool.

title: stuffed mushrooms with crabmeat
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
You also need one or two baking sheets, depending.

title: twelve can casserole
directions: Add all ingredients; mix.
Put in shallow baking dish; cover with second can of onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or at 250° for 3/4 hour, until topping is crusty.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pastry pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until soft. Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish and stir in cubed ham and cheese.
Make a white sauce by melting butter and blending in flour and adding milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thick.
Add soup and mix well.
Pour over noodles and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Mix the flour, baking powder and salt thoroughly.
Mix sugar, shortening and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Mix in bananas.
Add dry ingredients; stir just until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake until firmly set when lightly touched in center top, 50 to 60 minutes.
(Bread may crack across top.)
Cool on rack.
Remove from pan after 10 minutes.
Store in refrigerator to keep moist.

title: sweet-sour carrot slices
directions: Peel and cut carrots into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain, saving 3/4 cup.
Add this water to sugar, vinegar and mustard seed.
Add carrots and bring to boil.
(Tie spices in a bag, I use a tea ball.)
Simmer 10 minutes.
Chill in "fridge." Drain before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and serve with rye bread, veggies, Doritos or crackers.

title: diabetic or no sugar fruit cake
directions: Combine raisins, dates, figs, apricots and orange rind in small bowl.
Set aside.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir in flour, soda, baking powder and spices. Pour in fruit mixture and beat until blended.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container for 3 days.

title: lillie's lemon pie
directions: Bring water to boil; mix sugar, flour and little of lemon rind.
Pour dry ingredients into boiling water. Cook until thickened; set aside.
Beat egg yolks, rest of lemon juice and a little water; stir together and add butter and pour into shell. Top with egg white.

title: brandie's ham and cheese bites
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Split rolls and spread with mixture.
Layer chopped ham across bottom layer of rolls.
Top with top layer of rolls.
Sprinkle with grated Swiss cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° under foil tent.
Serve hot.

title: bread dip
directions: Combine all ingredients (spinach, soup mix, mayonnaise and sour cream) and put into a hollowed out loaf of Hawaiian sweet bread.
Save the bread pieces for the dip.

title: southern pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Blend other ingredients.
Arrange chops in baking dish and cover with blended mixture.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crackle top ginger cookies
directions: Chill well.
Roll in sugar and bake.

title: chocolate buttercream frosting
directions: Beat margarine, salt and 1 cup sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in chocolate.
Add rest of sugar, alternating with milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
If using cocoa, use full stick of margarine.

title: american chop suey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry hamburg and onions until brown. Add salt and pepper to hamburg.
While frying hamburg, boil macaroni until soft (10 to 12 minutes).
Drain macaroni and put in a greased casserole bowl (large).
Add condensed tomato soup, ketchup and hamburg mixture to macaroni and stir until well blended.
Put in oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.
(Tastes even better the next day!)

title: nine day slaw
directions: Blend sugar with chopped cabbage, pepper and onions.
Bring remaining ingredients to a full boil and pour over chopped cabbage mixture.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 9 days.

title: tomato-basil bruschetta
directions: In small bowl, combine olive oil and garlic; let stand 15 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine tomatoes, onion, basil, vinegar, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons garlic oil.
Stir gently to mix. Let stand 15 to 30 minutes, allowing flavors to blend.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Saute rice, mushrooms and margarine for 10 minutes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add the 2 cans consomme.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute. Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done. Adjust ingredients according to number of servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bananas, until moist.
Mash bananas and fold into mixture.
Pour into a greased (8 x 4-inch) loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: banana slush(serves 50)
directions: Blend bananas together in food processor.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Freeze mixture in plastic cartons.
Before serving, thaw to slush (1/2 to 3/4 hour).
Add 6 (2 liter) bottles of 7-Up.

title: spinach and strawberry salad
directions: Place strawberries, onions, and mushrooms in bottom of dish. Make a dressing of vinegar, honey, and mustard; pour over strawberries, onion, and mushrooms. Place chopped spinach and nuts on top. Let set in refrigerator overnight; toss the next day and serve.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine first five ingredients and set aside.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses. Gradually add flour
mixture.
Form into small balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: double chocolate fudge brownies
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Heat until bubbles form, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until spreadable. You may have to add 1 or 2 more tablespoons of milk to make spreadable.

title: pickled baby corn
directions: Boil vinegar in a nonaluminum pan. Bring enough water to a boil to cover corn. Add washed fresh corn and cook 2 minutes. Remove from water and drain. Boil vinegar with sugar, salt, spices and 1/2 water for 10 minutes. Pack corn into hot sterilized jars. Fill jars with vinegar mixture. Seal. Process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and melted margarine.
Press mixture onto bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Fill with your favorite chiffon or cream pie filling.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll into bite-size balls.
(Can be wrapped and frozen at this stage.)

title: angel hash
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Combine in saucepan the cornstarch and sugar.
Blend egg yolks and 1 cup of combined juices; add to sugar mixture.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove and cool to room temperature.
Fold in whipped cream, nuts, marshmallows, fruit cocktail, crushed pineapple and bananas.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken and remove meat from bones.
Mix stuffing mix, melted butter and 1/2 cup chicken broth in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Alternate layer of chicken and dressing.
Add 1 1/3 cups of chicken broth from which chicken was cooked.
Pour over mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken with dried beef
directions: Arrange dried beef
in	bottom	of
shallow
casserole. Wrap bacon around chicken;
arrange over beef; spread undiluted soup over chicken.
Cover with
foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: summer elegance(strawberries and cream)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions.

title: hot tuna sandwiches(serves 6)
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on 6 buns.
Close buns and wrap in foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Put cream cheese in bowl.
Add gelatin and milk.
Beat with wire whisk until blended and smooth. Chill.

title: double chocolate cupcakes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine orange juice, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Fold in chocolate morsels.
Spoon into lined muffin pan, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans immediately; cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: finnish summer soup
directions: Heat water to boiling in 5-quart pan.
Add potatoes.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes.
Add onions, carrots, green beans and garlic powder.
Add basil, if desired.
Add margarine; simmer for 8 to 10 minutes more.
Add peas and cook for 2 to 4 minutes or until they are crisp-tender.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl or large roasting pot add meat, onion, green pepper, garlic powder, salt, pepper, oregano and onion salt.
Add crackers, 1/2 cup ketchup and eggs.
Top meat loaf with rest of ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Lightly mix tuna fish, peas, mushroom soup and egg noodles in buttered casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cover with a layer of crushed potato chips.
Bake in medium oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain well.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oleo.
Stir in cheese to drained broccoli.
Add vegetables and stir with undiluted soup into the rice.
Put in shallow dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat 2 minutes.
Add potatoes and heat until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to potato mixture.
Blend well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put in greased loaf pans, 10 1/2 x 16 1/2-inches.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Can be served warm with a dab of whipped cream or frost with your favorite icing.
Serves 100.

title: chocolate cream cheese layer cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips in 1/4 cup hot water.
Mix together all the ingredients and melted chocolate.
Divide mixture in half (about 3 cups), 1/2 will be used for frosting.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: stoney creek school barbecue chicken
directions: Brush on chicken with every turning until tender.
Then use second sauce for at least 2 coats.
(Watch carefully as it scorches easily.)

title: sweet pickled cauliflower
directions: Prepare vegetables in separate containers.
Cut cauliflower flowerets in medium pieces. Slice celery and onions in thin slices; slice peppers in rings, strips or pieces.
Cut baby carrots in half.
Let vegetables and salt stand covered with cold water for 6 hours or overnight.
Drain and rinse vegetables.
Make a syrup with sugar, vinegar and spices.
When sugar is dissolved, add celery, carrots and lima beans.
Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add cauliflower, peppers and onions; cook until all vegetables are crisp, yet tender.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars, cover with syrup and seal.

title: white cake icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, 1 cup at a time.
Beat well on medium speed.
When all sugar has been mixed, mixture will appear dry.
Add milk.
Beat at high speed until fluffy.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple (juice included) and jello until boiling.
Cool in freezer until partially congealed.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk with mixer.
Combine with pineapple mixture and pour into oblong Pyrex dish; refrigerate.

title: herbed taters
directions: Wash potatoes; peel strip around center.
Place in crock-pot; add water.
Cover and cook on high 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: stuff-mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Remove stems from mushrooms and stuff with crab mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Beat together all ingredients and pour into 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake until firm, about 20 minutes.
Serve warm with black walnut ice cream.

title: finger jello
directions: Stir all
ingredients.	Pour
into
a
9 x 13-inch pan. Chill. Cut
into	small squares.	Use smaller pan for thicker squares. Kids love these and they are not sticky.

title: doris' oyster fritters
directions: Mix ingredients and fry in oil.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt until sugar is dissolved. Continue cooking without stirring until syrup forms brittle ball in cold water.
Add vanilla; stir only enough to mix into hot syrup.
Pour syrup slowly over popcorn, mixing well. Shape into balls.
Use butter to coat hands before shaping popcorn balls.

title: rum cake
directions: Place chopped pecans in bottom of greased Bundt pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Cook:
Stir-fry chicken until done. Remove from pan.
(Cook garlic in with chicken.)
Stir-fry rest of ingredients approximately 3 minutes or until celery is crisp-tender.
(Remove from skillet; blend into chicken.)

title: ham strata
directions: Combine the last 5 ingredients.
Layer in a 10-inch pie plate 1/2 of bread cubes, 1/2 of broccoli, cubed ham, Swiss cheese, other 1/2 of broccoli, 1 tablespoon dried onion (or 1 teaspoon fresh) and other half of bread cubes.
Pour egg mixture over all. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: minty cool dessert
directions: Thaw Cool Whip, then add some creme de menthe (usually a small amount) until Cool Whip tastes minty.
Shave some chocolate curls onto the top of the Cool Whip.
Use cookies or fruit to dip for a light, tasty dessert.

title: cocoa crispy bars
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with nonstick spray. Melt the butter and chocolate in a large saucepan over low heat. Add the Marshmallow Creme, cocoa and vanilla; stir until smooth. Remove from heat and add the cereal, stirring until well-coated. Spread the mixture into the prepared pan. Spray your hands with nonstick spray and press the batter down evenly. Let cool 10 minutes, then cut into 24 squares.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Make jello, but only add 1 cup cold water after adding boiling water.
Immediately after jello dissolves, add jellied cranberry sauce; stir and mash up sauce well.
When cooled, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or any mold and chill.
Serve with turkey or ham.

title: rocky road s'more bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined flour and crumbs; mix well.
Press onto bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Put crescent rolls in jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inches).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes; cool.

title: salsa (hot sauce)
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion and pepper.
Mix with salad oil, lemon and seasonings.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese; add salt.
Work in flour; roll and cut.
Bake in preheated 350° oven.

title: curried chicken skillet dinner
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; sprinkle 1 tablespoon seasoning mixture over chicken, tossing to coat.
Reserve remaining seasoning mixture.
Bring chicken broth, orange juice, rice and reserved seasoning mixture to boil in large nonstick skillet.
Add chicken; reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in peas, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Yields 4 servings.

title: smoothies
directions: Put berries, bananas and dates in blender with enough pineapple juice to make blender work.
Garnish with fresh berries or touch of toasted coconut.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Scrub cucumber; grate unpeeled cucumber and drain until almost dry.
Combine with other ingredients.
Chill before serving.

title: chicken broccoli oriental
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken until brown.
Add onions, pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until tender. Stir in soup, water and soy sauce; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover to simmer.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: ham and asparagus pie
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in next 3 ingredients. Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sauce comes to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Stir small amount of sauce into mayonnaise, then stir into mixture in saucepan.
Add ham, asparagus and lemon juice; cook until heated.
Turn into pie shell.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Broil about 2 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: play dough
directions: Boil on stove 4 cups of water and cooking oil.
Add few drops of food coloring of your choice.
Add flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Stir on low heat until ball like consistency.
Roll and knead until play dough.

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Brown hamburger; break up and drain.
Saute onions and peppers until tender and add to meat.
Add all spices and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes; simmer about 30 minutes in a stainless steel pan, stirring often.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix macaroni with meat sauce.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch or larger casserole pan.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 and reheats well.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler. Add can of tomatoes and peppers. Serve warm.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together.
Let stand in fridge overnight.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Slightly cook onion; add to hamburger and brown together.
Pour off any grease.
Add remaining ingredients, including all juice from beans.
Mix well.
Place in crock-pot for a couple of hours on high or bake, covered, at 300° for a couple of hours (it should be juicy).

title: crunchy broccoli and cauliflower toss
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Pour dressing over vegetables; toss lightly to coat.
Cover and chill overnight.
Yields 6 servings.

title: oven fried catfish
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Mix corn meal, bread crumbs and spices. Dip fish in milk, then in corn meal mixture. Place fish in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Pour margarine over fish. Bake, uncovered, about 17 minutes until fish flakes.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Cut up hearts into 4 pieces and mix with mayonnaise and cheese.
Place in a small heat-proof dish.
Bake at 325°, covered, for 20 minutes and 1 minute under broiler, uncovered, to brown top.
Serve from the oven with crackers.

title: grilled whiskey chicken
directions: Rub chicken pieces with the lemon.
Mix other ingredients together.
Marinate chicken 2 hours or more.
Grill chicken 20 minutes per side.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla in top of double boiler.
Use mixer to stir.
Beat briskly for 3 minutes or until frosting is fluffy and holds its shape.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Yields enough for two 9-inch layer cakes.

title: raspberry champagne punch
directions: In blender container, puree raspberries.
In large punch bowl, combine pureed raspberries, lemon juice, sugar and wine; stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, scoop sherbet into punch bowl; add sparkling wine.
Stir gently.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat milk and margarine. Beat eggs and sugar together. Add vanilla and beat well. Pour egg mixture into warm milk and margarine. Pour into deep uncooked pie crust. Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 15 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts; blend. Place shortening in mixing bowl and heat until creamy and glossy. Gradually add sugar to shortening, beating until light and fluffy after each addition.
Add eggs and beat until thick and pale lemon in color.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately.
Blend thoroughly after each addition.
Fold in fruits, peels and raisins.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, cheese, mayonnaise and 1 cup crackers.
Put in casserole.
Top with crushed crackers by hand, not fine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: alma's chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into buttered casserole dish (8 x 10-inch).
Melt 1 stick oleo and mix with package of stuffing.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: club favorite spinach
directions: Fold sour cream and soup mix into cooked, drained and seasoned spinach.
Bake in casserole for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, until hot.
Serves 6.

title: old fashion nut cake
directions: Boil 3 minutes; let cool.
Then add 3 1/2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon soda.
Mix; then add in large bowl of nuts or more.
Spoon mixture into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together.
Mix in remaining indredients and let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots into rings, boil until just tender in salt water. Pour in colander and cool.
Put next 6 ingredients in blender and blend.
Dice pepper and separate onions into rings.
Layer carrots, pepper, then onions.
Pour sauce over all then marinate for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: granola
directions: Mix vanilla, oil and honey; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Spread in large baking dish and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking period. Remove from oven and add 4 ounces raisins, 1/2 cup raw sugar and 1/2 cup each of coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Serve.

title: grandma's raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, slightly beat egg yolks.
Beat in butter until blended.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add pecans and raisins, vinegar and vanilla. Mix well.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Chop Oreos into crumbs.
Melt butter and mix with crumbs. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1/2 cup of crumbs to put on top.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Spread this over crumbs and chill for 20 minutes. Prepare pudding mixture, using 2 1/4 cups milk.
Spread over the mixture and chill.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over this and sprinkle the rest of crumbs on top.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and milk until thick.
Stir in peanut butter and mix well.
Pour into greased dish.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Cut marrow into 1 1/2-inch pieces; do not wash after cutting; cut kidneys, heart, liver, sweetbreads and brains into 1-inch cubes.
Put heart, kidneys, marrow guts, onions and salt and pepper in enough water to cover.
Cook until nearly done.
Add sweetbreads, bread, liver and brains.
Cook until marrows are tender.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean spinach.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Place in bowl. Top with strawberries.
Pecans can be toasted in saucepan with melted butter.
Stir constantly.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Layer half of cake cubes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, combine pudding, sour cream and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour half of mixture over cake cubes.
Spread 1 can of cherries over mixture.
Repeat second layer.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Can be topped with ice cream.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Place in a large salad bowl.

title: peanut butter popcorn balls(microwave)
directions: Place popped corn in buttered 4-quart bowl and set aside. Unwrap caramels and place in 1-quart glass mix and pour bowl.
Add butter. Microwave on High, uncovered, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until caramels are melted, stirring once.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over popped corn.
Mix lightly until well coated.
Using buttered hands, form into 16 (3-inch balls).
Cool and wrap each in plastic wrap.

title: fruit roll
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide in 3 parts.
Roll into logs. Roll each log in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: eggs in bologna cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 6 muffin cups with some shortening, using pastry brush or paper towel.
Melt 2 teaspoons shortening in skillet over low heat.
Place 3 slices bologna in the skillet and fry until the edges curl and the centers puff.
Lift each slice with tongs into muffin cup and press down so the slices fit the cup.
Repeat with remaining bologna slices.
Break 1 egg into the center of each bologna slice to hold it down.
Pour 1 teaspoon milk over each egg.
Sprinkle eggs lightly with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are set.
Loosen each bologna cup with knife and lift to platter with spoon.

title: pumpkin pie(dieters)
directions: Add salt, spice, Sweet 'N Low and eggs to pumpkin gradually. Add milk.
Pour into a well-greased 8-inch pie pan.
Place in a shallow pan of water and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
While still lukewarm, slip the baked filling into the pie crust.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Microwave Directions:
In a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole, cook potatoes in 2 tablespoons of water, covered, on High for 11 to 13 minutes until tender.
Turn potatoes halfway through cooking.

title: curried chicken puffs
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, milk and seasonings and mix well.
Add chicken, almonds and onions and mix lightly.
Cut tops from miniature cream puffs.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Replace tops and bake at 375° for 5 minutes or until warm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing together.
Add dried beef; mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: steak smear to impress
directions: Grill sirloin steak to your taste.
Allow cheese and butter to get to room temperature.
Mix thoroughly.
Immediately smear on steak off the grill.

title: glorified rice
directions: The rice should be cooked until it is soft, but not mushy. Mix all ingredients except the whipped cream.
Let stand 1 hour. Fold in whipped cream.
Just before serving, garnish with candied cherries.

title: children's paint brush cookies
directions: Mix well with a spoon the shortening, sugar, 2 eggs and vanilla. Blend in the flour, baking powder and salt.
Place dough in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: cheese stuffed hamburger roll
directions: Simmer onions in 1/3 cup boiling water for 5 minutes; pour over bread.
Combine meat, eggs and seasonings.
Pat out in 14 x 8-inch rectangle on waxed paper.
Spread meat mixture over; sprinkle 1 cup of the cheese atop.
Roll.

title: golden glow salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add lemon juice and enough cold water to pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Stir into gelatin.
Chill until slightly set.
Stir in pineapple and carrots.
Pour into a 4 cup mold coated with nonstick cooking spray; cover and chill until firm.
Unmold.
Yield:
6 servings.
Exchanges:
1/2 fruit. Serving:
1/6 of recipe.
Calories:

title: corn casserole
directions: Pour in a greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and grate Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to a second boil.
Cover; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: shakertown's pumpkin muffins
directions: Cook, drain and mash the pumpkin; put it through a strainer. Set aside.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and 1/2 gallon of water.
Add pineapple juice and lemonade and fill the gallon jug to the top with water. Freeze until slushy.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and store in refrigerator at least 4 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water in a medium bowl and set aside to cool.
Tear cake into small pieces.
Press into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix whipped topping and cooled gelatin.
Fold in strawberry halves.
Pour over cake pieces in pan.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: beef and biscuits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onions; drain excess grease.
Add salt and pepper and chili powder.
In large mixing bowl, combine egg, tomato sauce, sour cream and all but 1/4 cup cheese; add beef mixture.
In glass baking dish, put 1/2 split biscuits on bottom; pour in beef-cheese mixture, cover with remaining biscuits.
Bake 30 minutes, adding remaining cheese during last ten minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Layer ingredients in order, excluding corn chips which will be used for dipping.
Use a shallow, ovenproof dish.
A quiche dish is perfect.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until hot.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Instead of this dressing, you can use Ranch dressing or creamy Italian dressing.

title: sunshine pickles
directions: Use large green cucumbers.
Peel slices lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cut slices 1-inch thick.
Cook in sugar syrup and spices until transparent.
Seal while hot.

title: plantation squash
directions: Cook squash.
Drain.
Add other ingredients except crumbs and cheese.
Mix well.
Put in casserole.
Add bread crumbs and cheese on top and bake at 375° until hot, about 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Mix ground chuck, onion, bell pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until done.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook until done.

title: biscuit bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a hot well-greased cast-iron skillet for 18 to 20 minutes at 400° or golden brown.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk; boil.
Reduce to medium; boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add oats and vanilla. Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: grandma ruthie's cranberry nut bread
directions: Makes 1 large (9 x 5-inch) or 2 small (7 x 3-inch) loaf pans. Line the pan(s) with greased wax paper.
In a mixing bowl stir together the dry ingredients.
Cut the margarine into the dry mixture.
In a separate bowl, combine the orange juice, grated rind and egg.
Pour the liquid mixture into the dry and mix just enough to dampen; do not beat.
Fold in the nuts (if adding) and cranberries.
The mixture will be stiff and hard to stir.

title: four layer delight
directions: Blend these ingredients and press into the bottom of a buttered baking dish (square or oblong size).
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Cool.

title: three bean bake
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion.
Mix rest of ingredients together, then mix with ground beef mixture.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: german hamburgers
directions: Mix the ingredients together with hands (moosh it together). Make patties and broil or fry on both sides.

title: creamy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken on all sides with onions in margarine.

Add tomatoes, green peppers, milk, seasoning and bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is tender. Uncover, continue cooking 10 minutes. Remove chicken to platter. Melt cheese with vegetables and serve over chicken.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake and cool crescent rolls.
Spread cream cheese, mayonnaise and dry Ranch seasoning on crescent rolls.
Top with fresh vegetables.
Put cheese on top.

title: oriental hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions, celery and soups.
Add water.
Stir in rice, soy sauce and pepper.
Put in greased casserole.
Cover and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover; cook 30 minutes.
The last 15 minutes, add noodles.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, water and flour and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into small balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in oven at 325° for about 20 minutes. Remove to rack.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
If desired, dip end of each finger in thin chocolate icing.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cold veggie salad
directions: Clean fresh veggies.
Cut cauliflower and broccoli into bite-sized flowerets.
Cut carrots diagonally.
Combine all veggies.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and garlic salt.
Add veggies and refrigerate.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce and simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: mound bars or balls
directions: Melt margarine, then mix in coconut, powdered sugar and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix together real good.
Put in a big bowl and then put in the refrigerator for about 3 hours or until real cold.
Roll in small balls or make bars about the size of your index finger. Lay on a sheet pan on wax paper.
Put in the freezer for about 3 or 4 hours or until frozen.
Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler. Put in wax (melt it good).
Drop balls or bars in.
Lay out on wax paper, then store in a sealed bowl.
May need to keep heating chocolate.

title: corn and oyster casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a large bowl, saving 1/2 cup cracker crumbs for topping.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup cracker crumbs mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook chopped onion in oil until tender.
Add sausage and cook; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: depression stew
directions: Mix well the tomato soup and water.
Cut vegetables into chunks.
Brown meat.
Drain off grease.
Put meat in Dutch oven. Layer meat and vegetables.
Pour over the soup/water.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until vegetables are tender.

title: imperial crab meat
directions: Saute green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour and add milk gradually to make a cream sauce.
Remove from heat.
Add egg as mixture cools.
Add Worcestershire sauce, parsley and crab meat and blend.
Place in greased baking dish and bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chop suey
directions: Boil
the
bones off a turkey or chicken carcass.
Pick off meat.
Add	salt,
pepper and sage to taste to the broth. Stir in cornmeal until thick (very thick).	Pour in a buttered loaf
pan. Put
in freezer until hard enough to slice.
Slice off
as needed. Roll in flour and fry until brown.
Serve for breakfast, lunch or dinner in place of meat.

title: mounds bars
directions: Press the first 3 ingredients into pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine corn, cabbage, peppers and onions, then add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bring to boil and simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Pour at once to overflowing into clean, hot preserve jars.
Cold pack for 30 minutes (30 minutes from the time the water starts to boil).
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: craft dough cutouts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Measure flour and add salt.
Gradually add water, stirring until a stiff dough forms.
If necessary, add up to 1/4 cup more water until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Place dough on lightly floured surface.
Knead for 5 minutes. Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out shapes and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake dough for 30 to 45 minutes or until light brown on edges. Cool completely. Paint with acrylic paint and/or polyurethane.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bring milk, sugar and vanilla to a boil.
Pour over cake while hot.
Let cake cool, then spread with large container of Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Brown sausage and add Cheez Whiz.
Split English muffins. Spread with sausage and cheese mixture.
Place on baking sheet; bake until hot and bubbly.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Good with grits and fresh fruit.

title: peanut butter hash
directions: Blend chocolate and peanut butter. Add other ingredients.
Mix and pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Slice when set.

title: italian beef
directions: In a roasting pan, spray first with cooking spray, sprinkle both sides of meat with salt, pepper, garlic and oregano.
Lay sliced onions and peppers on top of meat.
Pour broth, beer and pepper juices on top of meat.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.
When done, shred meat with 2 forks. Refrigerate broth mixture and skim fat when cool.
Add to meat mixture and reheat.
Serve on Italian rolls.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop onion in blender then add other ingredients.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Mix flour, salt and egg in a large bowl.
Add milk gradually. Beat in small amount of cold water; let stand.
Cover bottom of cake layer pan with a little oil and heat in oven until very hot (almost smoking).
Beat flour mixture again and add to oil.
Bake in hot oven at 450° to 500° for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot with roast potatoes and gravy (or you might like it spread with jam).

title: marinated broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine.
Pour over salad and marinate 24 hours.

title: cream of mushroom spaghetti
directions: Boil 3 cups of water in a large saucepan.
Place spaghetti in boiling water for 15 to 20 minutes; drain and set aside.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir well.
Drop on wax paper and let cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs with a wire whisk or fork.
Add salt, butter, syrup, sugar and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve a la mode, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: pecan shorts
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar and cream until light and fluffy. Stir in flour, water and vanilla.
Add nuts and mix well.
Form into 1/4 inch slices and bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 minutes.
While cookies are still warm, roll in sifted confectioners sugar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, salt and a dash of pepper.
Mix in broccoli and celery.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Dot with butter, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.
This recipe can be prepared ahead of time and left in the refrigerator until ready to cook.
A great company dish.

title: fried fresh corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain, crumble and set aside.
Drain all but 2 Tbsp drippings from skillet.

Add corn, water, sugar and pepper. Bring to boil over medium heat. Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring frequently to keep from burning. Combine cornstarch and 2 Tbsp cold water, stirring until smooth. Stir into corn mixture and boil for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Top with crumbled bacon before serving. Make 4 to 5 servings.

title: large chocolate cake
directions: Mix hot water and soda. Set aside. Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs then add remaining ingredients except for hot water. Beat with mixer until smooth. Slowly add water, beating on low with mixer. Put into 9 X 13 pan or 3 nine inch layer pans and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: cream gravy
directions: In a screw-top jar, shake half of the milk with flour, salt and pepper.
Add remaining milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: quick coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients for a few minutes in blender.
Pour in pie plate (buttered).
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, cheese and milk; pour over thawed hash browns.
Combine well.
Bake at 375° to 400° about 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla. Stir in flour and
cream	of
tartar. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Heat
oven	to
Divide dough into halves.
Roll each half on	lightly
floured
cloth covered board. Cut into shapes. Sprinkle
with sugar. Place on lightly greased sheet. Bake until edges are light brown, 7 to 8 minutes.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and vanilla in a large saucepan.

Bring to a boil, add pecans and cook to a soft ball stage (a few drops in a cup of cold water holds its shape). Remove from heat and add vanilla and beat by hand until creamy. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or spread in buttered dish working fast because it sets up real quick.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill well.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: fried chicken
directions: Place clean chicken in bowl of Worcestershire white wine sauce and keep in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Beat eggs with 1 tablespoon of water.
Mix dry ingredients.
Place chicken in egg, then flour and spice mixes.
Place again in egg mix, then flour mix again.
Fry until well done.

title: prawns galleo
directions: Saute the onions, garlic and parsley in the butter for one minute; add the prawns and flame with the brandy.
Add rest of the ingredients and simmer for another minute.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Combine shortening, cocoa, and eggs, mix well together.
Add soda, salt and sugar, beat well.
Add 1 cup of flour and 1 cup of buttermilk, mix well then add the rest of the flour and buttermilk.
Pour in pan and bake.

title: calico sage stuffing
directions: Combine giblets, except liver, and water in a large saucepan. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.
Add liver, celery, onion, carrot and parsley.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes more.
Drain, reserving 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Add margarine to reserved liquid; stir until melted.
Stir in sage, poultry seasoning, rosemary and sugar, if desired.

title: cabbage jambalaya
directions: Saute beef, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add tomatoes, chopped cabbage, rice and water.
Cover; cook slowly until rice is done.

title: salisbury steak
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, preheat broiler if manufacturer directs.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat on stove, in hot butter/margarine, cook onions until tender (about 5 minutes), stirring frequently.
Stir in cornstarch, salt, bouillon, bottled sauce for gravy and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Keep onion mixture warm.

title: fruit and cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and fruit.
Work in pudding.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll into 1 large ball.
Roll ball into chopped nuts.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together hot water, sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm water mixture, egg and half the flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover tightly with waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator until double in bulk, or until needed.
To use, punch down and cut off amount needed.
Shape as desired.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: citrusy party punch
directions: Pour ginger ale down sides of bowl.
Add fruit juices.
Stir up and down.
Put in 1 quart lemon or pineapple sherbet.
Serves 24.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together
pudding mix and milk according to package directions.
Add
Cool
Whip
and
vanilla.
Layer crackers on bottom of
dish, then 1/2 pudding mixture, then crackers, then rest of pudding mixture, then crackers on top, then glaze.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli; drain thoroughly.
Place broccoli in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and egg to mixture.
Stir until well blended. Pour over broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle evenly over soup mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes until crumbs are lightly brown.

title: parslied potatoes
directions: Peel a strip of skin from around middle of potatoes; place in cold water and set aside.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread evenly over peanut butter mixture.
Let stand 1 hour or refrigerate for approximately 15 minutes until chocolate looks dull.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Keep refrigerated.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In an iron skillet, mix dates, sugar, butter and egg over a low heat.
Cook until dates melt down and get mushy.
Turn off heat.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies and mix real well.
Roll mixture into small balls and roll in coconut.
Allow cookies to cool on wax paper.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream shortening, add just 1 1/2 cups sugar and beaten egg yolks. Cream well.

title: sweet potato apple pie
directions: In bowl, stir together flour and the first 1/2 teaspoon salt. Cut in shortening until piece are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of the water over part of the mixture; toss with a fork to moisten.
Add remaining water, a tablespoon at a time, tossing until all of the mixture is moistened.
Form into a ball, flatten on lightly floured surface.
Place pastry in a 9-inch pie plate; crimp edges high.
Place apples in bottom of pastry.
In bowl, combine potatoes, eggs, cream, brown sugar, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg; beat until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Cover edges of crust with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: wilma's bun recipe
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients and let cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs. Add rest of ingredients and beat with an electric mixer until you can't beat in anymore.
Then knead with hands until smooth.
Let this raise twice and then mold into buns or bread.
I use this for bread too.
Bake at 350° around 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in greased cake pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well with small amount of ketchup.
Shape into a loaf and put into a deep pan.
Cover loaf with ketchup and add water to cover half of the loaf.
Also add ketchup, pepper and salt (as desired) into water.
Cook for one hour at 350° in oven.
Add water as necessary.
Do not let pan become dry.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° about 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
A good party dish.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat a large frying pan.
Turn heat down to medium-high.
Add generous amount of olive oil.
When pan cools, add hot pepper rings and half of onion wedges.
Fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Add chicken chunks.
Fry until chicken is browned and almost cooked through. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add bell pepper chunks. Stir to incorporate.
Let peppers cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add marinara sauce.
Add wine.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down to simmer.
Add mushrooms and other half of onion.
Let simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with crusty bread.

title: the maples inn blueberry-stuffed "french toast"
directions: Arrange 1/2 the bread cubes in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan. Scatter the cream cheese over the bread; sprinkle blueberries over the cream cheese.
Arrange the remaining bread crumbs over blueberries.
In a large bowl, whisk together eggs, syrup and milk; pour the egg mixture evenly over bread mixture.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Bake, covered with foil, in the middle of a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 30 minutes more, or until it is puffed and golden.

title: cookies without sugar
directions: Put dates and raisins in 1/2 cup boiling water and let stand awhile, then drain.
Cream the butter and Sucaryl; add egg.
Sift flour, baking soda, spices and salt.
Add to the mixture.
Add vanilla, fruit and oatmeal.
Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes in a 350° oven until slightly browned.

title: creamy chicken lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna as package directs and drain. Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and saute mushrooms and onion 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cream cheese and bouillon.
Cook until cheese is smooth and bouillon is dissolved, stirring often.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, eggs, nutmeg and chicken, mixing well.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of noodles, chicken mixture and shredded cheese.
Repeat layering.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 to 10 more.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: grilled teriyaki steak
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pan and marinate steak for approximately 2 hours (1 hour on each side) in refrigerator.
In a hot skillet over medium heat, grill steak approximately 10 minutes on each side until done and serve.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.

title: cherry cheese dessert
directions: Press the first 4 ingredients into bottom of well-greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Add sugar to cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Spread pie filling over cream cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Form crescent rolls into a crust in a round pizza pan.
Top with meat, potatoes and Cheddar (to within 1-inch of edge).
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over the pizza.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: In an 8-inch skillet, cook and stir the meat, onions and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake until rice is tender. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine all ingredients except beets.
Stir over low heat. Add beets. Butter to taste (optional).

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven fried cod with tartar sauce
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Line a jelly-roll pan with foil.
Lightly grease foil.
Mix potato flakes, paprika, instant onion and salt on waxed paper.
Spread mayonnaise on both sides of fish.
Coat with potato-flake mixture.
Place in prepared pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden on the outside and opaque in center.
Serve with Tartar Sauce.

title: sweet corn salsa
directions: Cut raw corn off cobs. Combine all ingredients in saucepan over high heat and stir while bringing salsa to a boil.
When butter has melted completely and takes on look of light butter sauce, remove from heat and serve immediately.
Makes 3 cups.

title: beer-cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish, or generously grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: frozen pastry(makes 5)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together and blend in shortening. Add cold water, white vinegar and egg.
Beat with fork and add to flour mixture.
Again, mix with fork or hand well.
Shape into 5 balls.
Wrap in wax paper; chill 1 hour.
May be used fresh or frozen in ball or rolled out in pie tin and then frozen.

title: banana butter pecan cake
directions: Blend; beat 4 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: english walnut-chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add eggs and oleo.
Add walnuts, chips and vanilla.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 60 minutes at 325°.

title: coconut candy
directions: Mix sugar, coconut and 1 tablespoon milk.
Add 1 tablespoon of milk at a time until mixture will hold its shape, but is not too wet and sticky.
Dust each child's hands with confectioners sugar. Give each child a portion of the candy on a sheet of wax paper. Let the children shape candy into 1/2-inch balls and roll in cinnamon.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and flour.
Add eggs, then vinegar and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: squirrel stew
directions: Cut coon in half.
Wash good.
Put coon in large pot.
Cover with water and boil 30 minutes.
Pour water off.
Do this 2 or 3 times.
In last water, add salt and pepper.
Cook until tender; drain.
Grease large pan.
Put coon in pan and put sage on coon. Bake until brown on both sides.
Bake sweet potatoes around coon.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add salt and pepper to taste; drain.
Mix soups and sauce in saucepan; heat.
Crumble Doritos and place in bottom of deep casserole dish.
Put hamburger in, then top with sauce mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and continue baking until the cheese melts.

title: greek-style string beans
directions: Combine the green beans, oil, salt, pepper and onion in large skillet.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Simmer until tender.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients; store in an airtight container.
We usually use 2 tablespoons to a large mug or to taste.
Add hot water and serve.
Delicious!
Also good with a jigger of brandy or whiskey.

title: crab cakes
directions: Pick crabmeat, leaving in chunks.
Fold crabmeat into bread crumbs in which the parsley, salt and pepper have been mixed.
Beat together the egg, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise until smooth and lemon colored.
Pour over crab meat and bread crumb mixture.
Toss lightly.
Form into desired size.
Refrigerate for several hours before cooking.
Reshape crab cakes when ready to cook.
Fry in butter or shortening or try broiling them.
There is less grease and fat this way (very good).

title: barbecue slow cooker beans
directions: Brown about 6 slices of bacon in microwave until crisp.
Break into small pieces.
Pour grease from bacon over onion in a small bowl and microwave until tender. While bacon and onion are cooking, mix the rest of the ingredients together. Add bacon and onion.
Put in crock-pot and cook 4 hours on low.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, crumbs, onion, salt, ginger and milk. Shape mixture by rounded tablespoons into balls and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs.
Keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones; reserve 1 cup chicken broth. In large mixing bowl add chicken, soups, reserved broth, Veg-All, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix by hand.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Bisquick and milk.
Blend well.
Top pie with mixture.
Bake 45 minutes until crust is brown.

title: fried apples(servings:  6)
directions: In large skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Add apples and spices.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve hot.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes; drain.
Combine celery soup and sour cream in bowl.
Add carrots; fold in squash and onion mixture.
Combine butter and stuffing.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture in bottom of baking dish. Spoon in veggies; top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
This can be kept hot in a large party coffeepot for guests or a crock-pot.
Great for Christmas parties!

title: chili
directions: Mix all; simmer until onions are tender and spaghetti is soft but not gummy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all the fruit
together
in
mixing
bowl.	Take
a separate bowl; add the juices together and add 1 small package of instant vanilla pudding
to
the
juice.
Pour this mixture over the fruits.

title: turkey waldorf salad
directions: Put mayonnaise in large bowl.
Add lemon juice and pepper. Stir until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and chill 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13 inch cake pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cool slightly.
Beat eggs, add 1 c. brown sugar, baking powder, salt, flour, vanilla coconut and nuts. Pour over crust and bake 20-25 minutes more.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Separate crescent dough into 16 triangles.
Dip a marshmallow into melted margarine, roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place marshmallows on shortest side of triangle.
Fold covers over marshmallow and roll to opposite point, completely covering marshmallow and pinching edges of dough to seal.
Dip the roll in melted margarine and place margarine side down in deep muffin cup.
Repeat with remaining marshmallows.
Place pan on foil or a cookie sheet during baking to guard against spillage.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.

title: chocolate truffle pie
directions: In a bowl, combine wafer crumbs and butter. Press onto the bottom and up the sides of a 9-inch pie plate coated with nonstick cooking spray. Freeze for 30 minutes. Spread chocolate ice cream over crust; freeze for 1 hour or until firm.

title: popcorn cake(kids recipe)
directions: Combine margarine and marshmallows in large pot.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until marshmallows melt.
Add popcorn, peanuts and 1 pound gumdrops.
Blend well.
Press into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Chill until firm.
Invert on plate. May decorate with gumdrop flowers.

title: crusty garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
In a small bowl, combine the garlic and oil;
mix well.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Pour batter into 3 small pans (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch) which have been greased and floured well.
Sprinkle top with mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pan for 5 to 10 minutes, then remove.
If too cool difficult to get out.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Make a graham cracker crust and bake for 10 minutes.
Mix together powdered sugar with cream cheese and add milk.
Spread in pan and top with pineapple, bananas, strawberries, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries (if desired).
Refrigerate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes, onions and cut peppers in strips.
Combine in large pan and add salt with cold water and drain thoroughly.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In medium saucepan take butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil 2 minutes.
Then add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix together, then drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Cool and eat.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Layer on bottom of tube pan.
Melt butter and sugar together.
As one layer of biscuits is complete, spoon some of brown sugar and butter mixture over it.
Repeat 2 - 3 layers, using all of the butter and brown sugar mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Let set for 5 minutes, then invert onto plate.

title: grape delight
directions: Cream together cheese and sugar.
Stir in grapes with spoon. Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Serve immediately or chill for later.

title: ham-zucchini stir-fry
directions: In a wok or 10-inch skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil over medium-high heat until hot.
Add ham and stir-fry until lightly browned, 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove to a plate.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons oil to pan and, when hot, add zucchini, carrots, red pepper and onion.
Stir-fry until onion is softened, about 3 minutes.
Add water; cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes until carrots and red pepper are crisp-tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, cold water, oil and pumpkin.
Mix well and set aside.
In a separate bowl, sift flour. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add dry mixture to wet mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Divide batter among three greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix all the ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: summer berry pie
directions: Mix berries in a large bowl.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: orange balls
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl; add half of vanilla wafers.
Process until fine crumbs.
Remove crumbs; set aside.
Repeat procedure with remaining vanilla wafers; remove crumbs and set aside.
Add pecan pieces to food processor bowl; process until ground.
Combine crumbs, ground pecan pieces, powdered sugar, orange juice concentrate and butter in a large bowl; stir until blended.
Divide mixture in half.
Cover 1 portion with plastic wrap and set aside.
Shape remaining portion into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut or 2 cups toasted ground pecans.
(Orange balls will dry out quickly; roll immediately after shaping.)
Repeat procedure with remaining portion.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chips; pour in casserole dish.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and cover top with crushed potato chips.
