Put back in oven and bake 5 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Thoroughly combine eggs, sugar, butter, lemon juice and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into pie shell; bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: quick tater tot bake
directions: In a skillet, brown meat and onion.
Drain any fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Top with potatoes.
Combine soup and water, pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well and drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Cream margarine;
add
the
flour and 3/4 of the sugar; blend well.
Add	the
beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Add the milk, lemon juice and rind.
Beat the remaining sugar into the stiffly beaten
egg
whites
and fold them into the first mixture.	Pour into
greased
custard cups and place in a pan of hot water.
Bake in
a
moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool; unmold and serve with your favorite lemon sauce.

title: rhubarb punch
directions: Cook rhubarb in 4 cups of water until tender, about 10 minutes.
Put through coarse sieve; add sugar to hot liquid.
Stir until dissolved; add other juices.
Chill until ready to serve and add last 3 quarts of water or ginger ale.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: tuna dogs
directions: Mix together.
Put in hot dog buns.
Wrap in foil and heat in oven until warmed through.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Mash shrimp with fork.
Sprinkle with red pepper.

title: fantasy fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave
margarine
in
4-quart
bowl
on
High for 1 minute or
until	melted.
Add
sugar
and
milk;
mix
well. Microwave on High for 5 minutes until mixture begins to boil, stir after
3 minutes;
mix
well.
Scrape bowl and microwave 5 1/2 more minutes.
Stir after 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate or peanut butter pieces until melted.
Add remaining ingredients;
mix well. Pour
into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: pronto pups
directions: Set hot dogs out in advance so they will come to room temperature and have dry outer skin.
(I usually place on a paper towel.)
Pronto Pup batter will not stick to cold, wet hot dogs.

title: how to make self-rising cornmeal
directions: I always try to keep powdered milk on hand for cooking to save the homogenized milk for drinking.

title: rolled tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas.
Steam tortillas or place in microwave to soften (3 tortillas for 20 to 30 seconds). Spread the mixture on tortillas.
Roll and chill.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: brooke's cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Make cake mix as directed on package, using water, oil and eggs. Fill each cone about half full of batter. Stand cones in muffin pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick carefully inserted in center of cones comes out clean. Cool completely about 1 hour. Frost with frosting and decorate with assorted candies. Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: classic ham 'n cheese
directions: Makes enough canape spread for 24 Melba toast rounds or dry, crisp crackers.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Flour hands and mix until it forms a ball; divide in half.
Grease and flour 2 pie pans or square pans.
Press dough into pans to cover just the bottom.
Prick with a fork all over.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Watch carefully.
Cut into pieces and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
May serve with fruit of choice after baked.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops from pepper. Chop enough peppers to make 1/4 C. Boil whole green peppers in water for 5 minutes. Sprinkle inside peppers lightly with salt. Cook beef, onion, 1/4 C green pepper. Drain fat. Add undrained tomatoes, uncooked rice, water, salt, sauce, and a dash of pepper. Bring to boil, reduce heat. Cover and simmer 15 to 18 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir in cheese. Stuff peppers with meat mixture. Place in a 10 x 6 x 2 inch baking dish. Bake covered on 350 for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian chicken
directions: Use boneless strips of chicken breasts in the amount you need (can be made with any quantity).
Keep chicken moist and roll in flour.
Shake off excess; season with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Saute in margarine 2 minutes per side.
Roll in Parmesan cheese (fresh if possible).
Sprinkle additional Parmesan in bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken and sprinkle with more Parmesan.
Melt some margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be made ahead and also freezes well.
If freezing, do it after it has been sauteed and put in baking dish (before baking).

title: skor bar dessert
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Use one layer for this recipe; you may freeze the other layer for another dessert.
Cool cake; cut into cubes.
Mix pudding as directed on package. Beat candy bars until crushed into small chips.
In a large bowl, layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip and candy bars.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until yellow and thickens (will be white with flour until it thickens). Add the butter. Cool, then add the apples, one at a time.
Pour into Pyrex dish. Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Add the cherries.
May be served as a dessert or salad.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, cool, de-bone, and chop chicken.
In broth, cook celery and onions until tender.
Add noodles and cook till tender.
Mix milk, soup and eggs together.
Add to noodles and stir.
Add chicken and velveeta.
Cook on low heat until the cheese is melted.
Pour into 9x13 pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 350° till brown.

title: breakfast lasagna
directions: Cook sausage and drain well.
Spread bread with butter and cube.
Cover bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch dish with bread cubes. Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Cover with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over.
Cover and chill overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken breasts.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer soup and chicken.
Next, place the broccoli, then the stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, then 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer white bread, buttered on both sides,
on
bottom
of
pan.
Spread sausage over bread; then
add the
grated cheese.
Mix eggs, cream, salt, mustard and
chilies. Pour
over cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until light brown.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows on bottom of pan.
Thoroughly combine strawberries and syrup with dry Jell-O.
Set aside in larger bowl. Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter over marshmallows in pan.
Spoon strawberry mix evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: white chocolate mousse
directions: In top of double boiler, heat white chocolate and 1/4 cup of the cream until white chocolate is almost melted, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and stir constantly until all white chocolate squares are melted.
Set aside to cool (about 20 minutes) until room temperature, stirring occasionally.

title: red cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into 1/2-inch strips and place into saucepan with apples and remaining ingredients.
Simmer until cabbage is tender. May have to add more vinegar, sugar or salt for your own taste.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cooking oil, and mix well. Drop by tablespoon into 1/8-inch of hot cooking oil in skillet. Cook until golden brown on each side on medium heat.
Makes about 14 patties.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Cook and stir butter, sugar, eggs and chopped dates for about 5 to 7 minutes.
Add vanilla, corn flakes, Rice Krispies and nuts. Form in balls and roll in coconut.

title: cream puff ring
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil water and margarine.
Remove from heat, stir in flour to make a ball.
Beat in eggs 1/2 at a time until smooth.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet to form a ring.
Smear together and bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cut apart, remove wet stuff and then fill.
Vanilla pudding or chocolate pudding. Top with Cool Whip.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant up into bite-sized pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Put into pot with water to cover.
Add celery, carrots and onion.
Simmer until elephant is tender.
Season to taste.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut into 1/4 inch strips.
Set aside.
Combine 1/4 cup butter and next 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Gently stir in potatoes and cheese.
Spoon into a lightly greased casserole dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Combine 3 tablespoons melted butter and stuffing mix.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly in the middle at 350°.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut steak into thin strips.
It is easier to cut if partially frozen.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat in nonmetal pan; marinate overnight.
You can use any amount of meat, just make sure you increase marinade amount in order to cover meat. In morning, remove meat; pat dry.
Bake on cookie sheets 6 to 7 hours at 100°.
Turn oven off; let sit overnight.
Store in plastic bags.

title: butterscotch pie filling
directions: Take a 1/4 cup water and mix with brown sugar and butter. Bring to a boil.
Mix eggs, milk, cornstarch and vanilla, beating well.
Add it to the hot syrup mixture.
Heat until thick.
Beat egg whites for topping for pies.

title: beef dip
directions: Dice chipped beef and spring onions.
Mix with cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: spinach bacon quiche
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs; whisk in milk, 1 c. cheese, onion, bacon, salt, mustard, and paprika.
Add spinach.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 40 min. or until a knife inserted halfway between the center and the edge comes out clean.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
With fork, combine cheese with margarine.
Spread mixture on bread, using about 1 1/2 teaspoons per slice.
Sprinkle with paprika if desired.
Cut each slice into 6 sticks.
Place in single layer on large baking sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until brown and crisp.
Yields 96 sticks, 16 servings.

title: lo-cal chicken oriental
directions: Place chicken pieces, skin side up in shallow baking dish. Surround with pineapple chunks.
Mix pineapple juice with vinegar, soy sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, basting occasionally.
Add pepper strips. Combine cornstarch and water in cup.
Stir into liquid in baking dish and bake an additional 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in dish (I use a long Pyrex). Mix the salad dressing and sugar together. Pour over salad and top with the cheese. Keep in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: aubergine parmigiano
directions: Serve with pasta or rice and green vegetable or salad.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Brown meat, salt and pepper to taste.
Put in roaster and pour remaining ingredients over and bake until tender.
Remove from roaster and shred with 2 forks.
Put back in sauce.
Serve hot in buns.

title: heavenly vegetable casserole
directions: Steam first 3 ingredients for a few minutes.
Cook until thawed and separated.
Drain and cool.
Add green peppers and chopped onions.
Put vegetable mix in a buttered 3-quart shallow casserole.

title: creme puffs
directions: Heat water and butter in a saucepan until the water boils and the butter melts.
Lower heat and add flour and salt all at once. Beat vigorously until mixture leaves the sides of the pan.
Remove from heat and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until smooth.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet, forming 10 puffs.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
When cool, cut off tops and scoop out soft dough.
Fill with whipped cream or whatever you desire. Replace tops and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: poppy seed torte
directions: Mix together and line bottom and sides of pan. Save 1/2 c. for topping.

title: meat loaf florentine(low-fat)
directions: * One pound ground turkey may be substituted.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into a graham cracker crust or the crust of your choice.
Top with fruit.

title: kevin's chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add syrup and then flour, sifted with baking powder and salt.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan, which has been greased and floured, for 45 minutes at 350°.
The cake is very moist and can be served without being iced.

title: broccoli nut salad
directions: Mix together broccoli, onion, bacon, peanuts and raisins.
Two hours before serving, add Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Rub through fine strainer.
Melt butter in heavy pan and cook onion without browning.
Blend in flour.
Add chicken stock.
Cook a few minutes and add broccoli.
Mix well.
Slowly add cream until heated.
Add salt and pepper if needed.
Serve hot or cold.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles for 10 minutes.
Drain and add all other ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into loaf pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet 'n sour chili
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil, then simmer for hour.
Good served over Cheddar broccoli rice (Lipton).

title: taco salad i
directions: Layer the ingredients in a large bowl.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Toss ingredients just before serving.

title: aunt lulu's grit bread
directions: Select 6 ears corn just beyond the "milk stage."
Cut off cob and remove all juice from cob; as you would for cream-style corn. Should have about 2 1/2 cups.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together over the raw corn; mix thoroughly.
Stir in egg alternately with melted shortening.
No liquid is necessary.
Bake in shallow pan 30 to 35 minutes at 425°.
Serve hot with butter. Serves 6.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Combine pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over baked bottom layer after it has cooled.
Heat pineapple juice and dissolve Jell-O in it.
Add frozen strawberries and mix well. Pour over other layers.
Chill until top is set.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9x13 pan.

title: punch(red)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze 1 package Kool-Aid in mold without sugar.
Add to punch for ice.

title: old oregon trail potato doughnuts(prize recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand in Oregon kitchen atmosphere for 15 minutes.
Make quite stiff, or they will not puff up as they should.
Fry in deep fat made of Nugget Brand lard.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Thaw pie crust for 10 minutes.
Prick bottom and sides of pie crust with fork.
Bake the pie crust on cookie sheet for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning mix to meat according to package directions.
In small bowl, combine refried beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce.
Mix well.
Layer half of refried bean mixture in bottom of pie crust; top with half of seasoned meat, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and all the chips.
Repeat layers.
Bake on preheated cookie sheets for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomato and taco sauce to taste.

title: chili(heart healthy)
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, melt butter and saute onions until shiny and tender.
Crumble in ground beef.
Brown well, stirring until no longer pink.
Sprinkle seasoning over.
Mix.
Add tomatoes, kidney beans and ketchup.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well; serve with vegetable cuts.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion.
Drain and place in casserole dish. Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and place over sausage.
Heat soup and milk together. Beat eggs and slowly add to soup mixture.
Remove soup from heat and beat well. Add cheese to mixture and stir until melted.
Pour over sausage and macaroni.
Top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour, salt and sugar.
Cook until bubbly.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Stir in corn.
Stir in eggs that have been beaten until frothy.
Pour into well-buttered casserole and set in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° about an hour.

title: spiced peach salad
directions: Prepare gelatin by package directions using peach liquid as part of water.
Stir in cheese.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until partially thickened.
Add chopped pecans and peaches.
Pour into lightly greased mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaf topped with mayonnaise.

title: play dough
directions: In a saucepan, combine dry ingredients.
Mix in wet ingredients and cook at medium heat for about 3 minutes or until edges look dry.
Stir into ball and dump on wax paper. Immediately put water in the pan; it will be easier to wash. Knead the dough while still hot and until salt crystals are gone. Store in airtight container.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut
round
steak
in
serving	sizes.	Salt and pepper steak and
roll in flour.
Brown in skillet with a little oil. Place steak
in crock-pot.
Mix soup, water and sauce and pour over round steak.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 5 hours.

title: disappearing chocolate cake
directions: Generously grease and flour two (9-inch) round cake pans. Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in eggs.

title: rice-mushroom casserole
directions: Put rice, onion soup mix, mushrooms and water into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle oregano on top.
Slice stick of margarine and distribute.
Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Crisco and eggs.
Add the eggs.
Add enough buttermilk to make the batter soft enough to roll out in hand.
Fry in Crisco shortening until brown.

title: salsa dip with meat
directions: Warm tomatoes, salsa and cheese until cheese melts. Serve with chips.

title: navajo fried bread
directions: This bread can be used for a side dish, tacos or sandwiches. Some people eat it as is, others put butter and syrup on it.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup Colby cheese; mix well.
Turn into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining cheese; bake 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sole in lemon parsley butter
directions: Place margarine in an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Microwave 1 minute or until melted.
Blend in cornstarch, lemon juice, parsley flakes, celery salt and pepper.
Dip each fillet in seasoned butter.
Arrange fillets with thick edges toward outside of dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 6 to 7 minutes or until fillets flake easily.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples with lemon juice, making sure all sides are covered.
Arrange apples in rows in 7 x 10-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Mix dry milk, lemon rind, cinnamon, Sugar Twin and brown Sugar Twin.
Sprinkle on apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix in a bowl the flour, dry milk, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and the nutmeg.
Mix dry ingredients and butter with a fork until crumbly.
Put into a greased baking dish the sliced apples, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of apples.
Bake near center of oven for 45 minutes, or until apples are tender (oven temperature at 325° to 350°).

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Sift next 5 ingredients together.
Add second mixture to first mixture.
Add nuts and pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
After cake is cool, spread with cream cheese frosting.

title: spam burgers
directions: Chop or grind up 1 can of Spam (fine).
Chop up/blend 1 small onion or 1/2 cup.
Use pre-grated cheese or grate up 4 ounces of cheese.
Stir up and mix all ingredients into a medium bowl. Separate the buns and split the tops and bottoms apart and spread the mixture about 1/4-inch thick on each bun half.
Set oven to broil or put the Spam burgers into the broiler or a toaster oven for approximately 5 minutes or until you see they are turning light brown.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 people.
Preparation Time:
10 minutes.
Total Time:
15 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: In a 4 qt. Dutch oven, melt margarine.
Add onion, green pepper and ham.
Brown.
Add potato, water and pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Make a paste of flour and 1/3 cup of water.
Add to potato mixture.
Add both cans of soup and drained corn.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: hot dogs in crock-pot
directions: Cut hot dogs in halves.
Cut bacon strips in halves.
Wrap each hot dog with a strip of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Mix ketchup and brown sugar together.
Pour over hot dogs; put in crock-pot. Simmer on low for approximately 8 hours.

title: homemade tomato juice
directions: Wash and crush tomatoes thoroughly.
In large pan add tomatoes and 1/2 water to each quart.
Add herbs to taste.
Heat slowly to 180° until liquid.
Through strainer cloth pour into glass or enamel container and let stand 24 hours in cool place.
Syphon off clear juice.
Strain again.
Heat to 180° adding 1/2 cup sugar for each quart.
Pour into sterile jars and process again to 180° for 20 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon coarse salt per jar before sealing.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Split Twinkies in half lengthwise. Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix pudding as directed and pour over Twinkies. Slice bananas over top of pudding. Pour cherries on top of bananas. Top with Cool Whip and nuts. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: bread custard pudding
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan with margarine.
Cover bottom with bread crumbs.
Heat milk.
Beat eggs and add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add milk slowly, beating all of the time.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Add nutmeg on top.
Bake at 300° until set (40 to 50 minutes).

title: busy day macaroni(cooked in microwave)
directions: Combine macaroni. water, sauce, and browned ground beef in 3 Qt. casserole.
Stir and cover, microwave on High for 14 minutes. While standing, sprinkle with cheese. The cheese will melt during standing time.

title: grandma's pickles
directions: Use large cucumbers. Peel and slice lengthwise. Place cucumbers in large container. Cover with water and add lime. Let stand 24 hours. Rinse thoroughly. Cover cucumbers with fresh water. Add alum and let stand 6 hours. Rinse and let stand in fresh water for 6 hours.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
When hot, pour flour in slowly and stir until flour turns brown.
Dice seasonings and saute in roux mixture.
Add 4 to 5 cups hot water and Tony's seasoning.
Add crab meat.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook another 30 to 45 minutes.
Let sit for a couple of hours.

title: popovers
directions: Beat eggs and add milk, shortening and dry ingredients in a blender.
Beat until smooth.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full and bake in preheated oven at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Serve with butter and jam or jelly.

title: petite cheese cakes
directions: Cream until fluffy the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Add egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes in paper-lined muffin tins (2/3 full).
Remove from oven and allow to "sink in."
Frost with sour cream mixed with 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Cool and freeze, muffin tins and all.

title: asparagus and yellow bell pepper with balsamic vinaigrette(6 servings)
directions: Cook asparagus in large pot of boiling salted water until tender, but still firm to bite, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Transfer asparagus to bowl of ice water and cool.
Drain well.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda.
Cream peanut butter and butter together.
Mix white and brown sugars.
Add all mixes together. Bake at 375° until light golden brown.
Store in airtight container with a piece of sliced bread (to keep cookies fresh).

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour into bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour into pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine and add to softened cream cheese.
Add confectioners sugar to margarine/cream cheese mixture.
Spoon on top of cake batter.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in casserole dish. Put 3/4 package stuffing on top of butter. Mix squash, sour cream, soup, onion and green pepper together. Put on top of stuffing. Sprinkle top with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: puto(rice cake)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients; blend well.
Add a drop of food coloring (optional).
Pour over muffin pans, 3/4 full.
Steam for 12 to 15 minutes.
Philippines recipe.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Have sausage and cheese at room temperature. Mix all ingredients good.
Form into balls on baking sheets.
Bake at 450° for about 10 to 15 minutes, until brown.

title: grilled onion-potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; cut each into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Blend butter and onion soup mix; spread on one side of each potato slice. Reassemble potatoes; wrap each in foil, sealing well.
Bake on grill over coals for 45 minutes or until done, turning once.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Combine all and stuff turkey.
Bake until popcorn blows the ass off the turkey.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix well and pour in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake until bubbly.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Combine peanut butter, butterscotch morsels and chocolate morsels in a heavy saucepan.
Place over low heat and cook, stirring constantly, until melted.
Stir in peanuts.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry and combine with cheeses, olives, peppers and dressing.
Lightly grease a mini or regular muffin pan and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush lightly with oil.
Bake 5 minutes or until golden.
Remove from tins; place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine and mix well.
Spoon into lightly greased 3-cup casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: May vary quantities or vegetables.

title: orange-blossom muffins(as served at excelsior house in jefferson)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add sifted Biskit mix.
Stir in marmalade and pecans.
Grease muffin pans; fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Be sure to use small muffin tins.

title: hominy
directions: Soak corn in water and soda overnight.
Rinse good and cook 3 or 4 hours. You will need to remove husk before the corn.
The hominy is ready to use in your favorite recipe.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and cook to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat.
In a warm mixing bowl, combine marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Add cooked syrup and mix well.
Pour into buttered 6 x 10-inch pan.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: *Any leftover gravy can be substituted for milk or in addition if like more liquid.

title: mommy's fried chicken
directions: In a large plastic bag, mix all dry ingredients.
In a shallow dish, beat eggs, milk and crushed garlic.
Heat oil in a frying pan, with cover, until hot, 325° or medium-low.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple into a saucepan. Bring juice to a boil and pour over jello.
Cool slightly.
Add crumbled cream cheese, nuts, cherries, pineapple and Coke. Refrigerate to jell.

title: play bubbles
directions: Mix well; ready to play.
Store in glass jar.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, eggs, sugar, sour cream and vanilla. Then add the dry ingredients (after blending them together in a bowl or plastic Baggie).
Chill 1 hour or overnight.

title: pomegranate-cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions.
Dissolve sugar while jello is still hot.
Add all ingredients.

title: twinkie shake
directions: In a blender, add milk and Twinkies. Blend for 5 to 10 seconds.
Add Oreo cookies. Blend together. Add 3 cups vanilla ice cream. Blend until smooth. Pour in glass.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, 4 eggs, 3/4 cup oil and 7-Up together and bake according to directions on cake box.
Mix remaining ingredients together for icing.
Cook until smooth and add about 2/3 cup coconut to mixture.
Spread on top of cooled cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans if you like.

title: mouth-watering chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa together in a large saucepan. Add 1 cup milk. Beat egg yolks in with other cup of milk. Combine into saucepan with other mixture. Cook mixture, stirring constantly. As mixture thickens, add butter and vanilla. Pour into pie shell. Add meringue on top.

title: fillet of sole provencal
directions: Place fish in sprayed 9 x 13 baking dish.
Combine juice and oil and drizzle over fish.
Top with slices of tomato and onion. Combine all spices and sprinkle on top of tomatoes and onion. Bake uncovered 10-15 minutes or until fish flakes with fork. Serves 2.

title: zucchini and corn souffle
directions: Grate zucchini; sprinkle salt over zucchini and let sit for 1/2 hour, then squeeze out all liquid very well.
Saute lightly onion in butter or margarine.
Add flour, pepper and milk; cook with sauteed onions until thickened.
Separate eggs.
Combine zucchini, milk and onion mixture with shredded cheese, corn, egg yolks and salt to taste.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks and add to mixture, folding in last.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart greased casserole. Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350° until puffy and brown.

title: potato puff
directions: Blend potatoes with egg yolk and butter.
Beat until light and creamy.
Add parsley and cheese; fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Place in buttered 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix all ingredients (ex. popcorn and vanilla); cook until you get a soft ball formed in the cold water.
Then add vanilla and stir.
Pour onto popcorn.
Mix well.
Butter hands and form balls. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: zippy onion spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover; chill 1 hour.
Spread on crackers.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups spread.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; add sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add soda; stir until thick and foamy.
Pour over popped corn that has been placed in a grocery bag.
Fold down top and shake.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake and turn sack upside down.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Turn sack right side up and cook 40 seconds.
Shake. Spread to single layer on a foil pan.
Cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat each egg separately, then gradually add sugar.
Mix well and add milk, vanilla, salt and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and let chill for 30 minutes before making.

title: congealed carrot and orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water, diced orange sections and grated carrots.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into mold and chill until set.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: beet pickle jello
directions: Add one cup water to jello and stir until dissolved.
Add beet pickles and shredded pineapple.

title: lemon pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add lemon juice, cold water and egg yolks; stir in boiling water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to boil.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Stir in margarine until melted.
Remove from heat.
Pour into pie shell.

title: applesauce quesadillas
directions: Place 2 tortillas on an ungreased baking sheet. Spread each with applesauce. Sprinkle with cheese and cinnamon-sugar, if desired. Top with remaining tortillas. Brush tops with butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly brown. Cut into wedges. Yield: 16 wedges.

title: crunchy chocolate sauce
directions: In 2-cup glass measure combine milk and chocolate.
Microwave at High (10) for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir to blend well.
Add sugar; stir.
Microwave at High (10) for 1 to 2 minutes, until mixture boils.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir thoroughly. Serve warm or cool.
Makes 1 cup.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar, oil, pie spice, and eggs.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Add flour.
Bake 45 minutes to one hour at 350°.

title: avocado dip
directions: In blender grind together onion, peppers and garlic salt to a paste.
Mash avocados and add paste, chopped tomato and onion; add all together.

title: texas style french toast
directions: Mix milk, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon in large dish.
Dip sliced bread into mixture and fry over medium heat in a frying pan until brown.

title: harry's favorite fettucine alfredo with chicken and vegetables
directions: In skillet, cook vegetables in olive oil (2 teaspoons) and set aside.
If grill is handy, cook boneless breasts of chicken on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Set aside.
Otherwise use broiler.

title: pound cake
directions: In large bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs. Add cake flour and vanilla; blend well.
Pour batter into lightly greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated 325° oven 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 5 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush Waverly wafers in bottom of casserole dish.
Debone chicken and place on crackers.
Pour 1 stick melted oleo over this, then mix next 3 ingredients and pour over chicken and crackers.
Sprinkle a little paprika over this.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until bubbly.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade and milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate.

title: mile-high biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening until coarse.
Add egg and milk all at once.
Mix into a ball.
Turn dough out on floured board and knead 10 to 12 times.
Roll out to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and freeze.
When biscuits are frozen, store in plastic bag in freezer. To bake frozen biscuits, place on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Cream butter and mix flour and sugar and cream with butter or margarine.
Beat eggs and add together with all other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie and cook at 400° until top is lightly brown.
Reduce heat to 250° or 300° or cook until filling is slightly thick.
Take out of oven and it will finish cooking. Very delicious!!!

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Put 1 tablespoon sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and crumble in yeast.
Cream shortening and sugar; add milk.
Let cool and add 2 beaten eggs and yeast, then 4 cups sifted flour.
Add salt and 4 more cups of flour.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce and peas in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Then place a layer of salad dressing and top with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Add small amount of onion.
Do this until you have used all your ingredients.
Be sure to save enough cheese and bacon for top. Set in refrigerator until ready for use, then blend it together with salad tongs or fork.

title: chicken huntington
directions: Make cream sauce of butter, flour and cream.
Add the grated cheese, pimento and hot chicken broth and mix.
Add the chicken and macaroni (cooked tender, blanched and drained).
Season to taste with salt and pepper and place in buttered baking dish. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: enchiladas
directions: In a medium skillet, heat oil; dip each corn tortilla one at a time.
Let them soak on a paper towel.
Set aside.
Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Combine brown meat with Wolfe chili; add water and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Place equal portions of grated cheese in center of tortilla.
Roll tortilla to enclose filling.
Place in a baking dish seam side down.
Pour meat sauce mixture over enchiladas.
Top with chopped onion and remaining cheese.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: granny's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together: cocoa, sugar, flour, salt, and vanilla. Add mixture to milk and cook until thick.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins and drain.
Mix ingredients with mixer for a few minutes.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Melt butter; add water and sugar and bring to boil. Preheat oven to 350°. Open crescent rolls and flatten out each triangle. Place 1/4 peach on each crescent roll triangle and wrap. Place in dish just big enough to hold the wrapped peaches. Pour liquid over peaches. The liquid should almost cover the dumplings. Place in oven and bake until tops of dumplings are golden brown (20 to 30 minutes, depending on the oven).

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Pour cereal in a large bowl; pour melted mixture over cereal to completely coat cereal.
Put powdered sugar in bowl.
Pour chocolate coated cereal in bowl.
Shake bowl until completely coated.

title: praline butter chocolate torte
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans, greased and floured.
Cool.
Split layers to make 4 layers.
Beat brown sugar and whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Fill each layer with 3/4 cup of whipped cream mixture.
Frost top with remaining cream mixture. Garnish with whole pecans if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: chilled vermicelli
directions: Pour dressing into bowl and mix in all ingredients except vermicelli.
Drain and mix with vinaigrette.
Chill for 24 hours. Bring to room temperature before serving.
Serve as a side dish or appetizer.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and oil.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well. Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk. Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: parmesan toasts
directions: Halve bread lengthwise; rub with garlic.
Cut in 4-inch sections, then 4 x 1 x 1-inch sticks.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 2 minutes to lightly brown.
Cool half of bread; store airtight for another batch later in the week.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cook the meat with seasoning (season to your taste).
Then mix in the bell pepper, onion and tomato sauce.
Then simmer for 1 or 2 hours.

title: oven style peas
directions: In
a
1 1/2 quart casserole combine frozen peas, mushrooms, onions, butter, savory, water, salt and pepper.
Cover and bake at 350° until tender (approximately 45 to 50 minutes, stirring after 20 minutes).

title: braised rabbit
directions: Cut up rabbit; remove fat, wash and dry.
Mix flour, salt and pepper and roll rabbit in mixture.
Brown in Crisco.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with water and scrapings from browning pan. Add last 3 ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour; turn down to 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Crumble sausage in medium-size skillet.
Cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Spread bread cubes in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Mix together eggs, milk and seasonings.
Beat well and pour over sausage and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: bacon and egg salad sandwiches
directions: In bowl, combine chopped eggs, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; mix well. Stir in crumbled bacon. Layer egg salad, lettuce and tomato; top with remaining bread slices.

title: summer rice salad
directions: Combine rice, peas, celery, onions, tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream together and gently fold into rice mixture.

title: nachos
directions: Spread tortillas or chips in a black pan.
Cover with refried beans, hamburger and salsa mixed together.
Sprinkle with cheese. Top with onion and bell pepper if desired.
Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground meat.
Saute onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic until tender.
Pour excess grease off.
Add salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
(I add a teaspoon of sugar.)
Let simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: sugar-free cake
directions: Boil raisins and water together until water evaporates. Combine all other ingredients and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Bake in a loaf pan.

title: spanish chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil in large skillet.
Add onion, pepper and rice.
Cook lightly about 10 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Cover; simmer 40 minutes.
Check and stir lightly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy caesar dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until smooth.
Cover and chill.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Up to 1 hour before serving, combine coleslaw mixture, green onions, Ramen noodles (saving the seasoning mix for the dressing), almonds and sunflower seeds in salad bowl.
Cover and chill.
